title: toads
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and drop from teaspoon into very hot deep fat (370°).
Molasses gives a richer, more robust flavor than sugar.
A little cinnamon and nutmeg may be added if desired.
These are delicate and tender when first cooked.
A brief heating in the oven helps them the second day.

title: stuffed flounder or sole fillets
directions: Arrange fillets on large plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Set aside while you prepare stuffing.
Combine celery, onion and margarine in glass bowl.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes full power or until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs, lemon juice, parsley, thyme and salt.
Divide fillets into 4 equal parts.
Put stuffing on top and roll up.
You may fasten together with toothpicks.
Place in casserole dish.
To cook in microwave:
Cover with wax paper. Microwave 5 to 6 minutes, or until fish flakes easily.
To cook in regular oven:
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: weepless meringue
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a small saucepan, stirring over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 or 2 minutes or until thick.
Cool completely.

title: fresh asparagus sesame
directions: Steam asparagus until tender-crisp (about 8 minutes).

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, a little at a time, then the flavoring.
Add the coconut last.
Grease and flour tube pan ahead of time.
Pour batter into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out cake, cool a few minutes and punch holes in top of cake.
Pour on glaze (add the glaze to hot cake).
Punch holes in cake with toothpick.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Melt butter and pour on stuffing.
Put half of stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch pan; add zucchini mix over this.
Put last half of stuffing on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: magic chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa, baking powder and soda.
Mix sugar with salad dressing.
Gradually add the flour mixture to salad dressing mixture alternately with water.
Add vanilla.
Put in 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: amish country hot chocolate
directions: Mix in plastic bag.
Store in airtight containers.
Use 3 tablespoons to 1
cup
of hot water.
Place miniature marshmallows on top if you wish.

title: tuna cheese twist
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Mix tuna, olives, onion, celery, green pepper and 1/4 cup soup.
Mix Bisquick mix and 1/2 cup cold water until soft dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes. Gently form dough into a ball on floured, cloth covered board. Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into a rectangle, 14 x 11-inches; place on a cookie sheet.
Spoon tuna mixture lengthwise down center of rectangle.
Sprinkle with one cup of cheese.
Make cuts 2 1/2-inches long at 1 inch intervals on 14-inch side of rectangle. Fold strips over filling.
Mix egg and 1 tablespoon water; brush over dough.
Bake until light brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix remaining soup, remaining 1/2 cup cheese and the milk over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Serve over tuna twist. Serves 6.

title: grilled shrimp scampi
directions: In glass bowl, combine shrimp with remaining ingredients, except oil and paprika.
Thread shrimp on skewers; brush with oil and sprinkle with paprika.
Grill on preheated surface 4 inches from heat.
Turn frequently.
Cook 8 minutes.

title: oobleck(do not eat!)
directions: Add food coloring to water.
Then add cornstarch.
Mix by hand from the bottom by slipping fingers under.
Use like play dough.

title: pam's spinach margarita
directions: Cut the steak lengthwise into strips 1 1/2 inches wide, then crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Seed, de-rib and cut the peppers into 1/2-inch strips.
Cut tomatoes into small wedges.

In large bowl, mix soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and water to smooth paste. Add steak slices; toss with large spoon to coat them thoroughly. Steak may be cooked at once or marinated in refrigerator for several hours.

title: pork 'n beans salad(delicious for cook-outs!)
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
The colder, the better.
Stir before serving.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain fat. Add tomato sauce and cheese. Simmer until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally. Add canned mushrooms. Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and rinse. Mix with sauce and pour into large casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until light brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix ARGO corn starch, sugar and salt in double boiler top. Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thick enough to mound slightly when dropped from spoon. Cover; cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Stir a little hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then stir all into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from boiling water.
Stir in vanilla and 3/4 c. coconut. Cool to room temperature.
Turn into pastry shell.

title: apricot salad
directions: Put Jell-O, sugar and water in pan.
Bring to boil.
Take off heat and dissolve cream cheese in mixture.
Then add apricots and pineapple.
Chill.
Beat the chilled milk and fold into mixture. Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: hot couscous
directions: Saute the vegetables and garlic in the oil for several minutes.
Cook couscous in chicken broth in a separate pan.
Add the chickpeas and the spices to the vegetables, and then add the cooked couscous.
Cook until everything is hot completely through. Garnish with grapes.

title: burgundy beans(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Wash beans; place in 5-quart saucepan and add 5 cups hot water. Simmer beans for about 1 1/2 hours.
Saute beef and chili powder until grey in color, breaking up well.
Add to beans along with tomatoes the wine, onion, garlic and salt.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours longer or until beans are desired doneness.
Just before serving, stir in diced cheese.
Let stand covered a few minutes to melt cheese.

title: safer's caesar salad
directions: Mix all together, except cheese.
Rinse lettuce and dry well; break into bite size pieces.
Take egg; dip in boiling water for 20 to 30 seconds (coddling egg).
Crack into dressing.
Mix together.
Pour over lettuce and toss.
Add cheese, then croutons.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Drain pineapple well and save juice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in casserole.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Heat oil to medium heat in nonstick pan.
Add onion, green pepper and cumin.
Cook 5 minutes sprinkling with bean liquid to prevent sticking.
Stir in corn. Spoon green pepper mixture, beans and cheese on each flour tortilla.
(Divide ingredients equally.)
Fold tortillas over to enclose filling.
Place in baking pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 450°.

title: zucchini rice tomato casserole
directions: Saute garlic in oil on low heat; add tomatoes and simmer with Italian seasoning, salt and pepper for 1 hour.
Add rice and water if needed.
Wash and slice zucchini.
Add to rest of ingredients. Simmer until well done.
Add cheese when serving.
Great with Italian bread; makes a meal in itself.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Combine cheeses, milk and butter in double boiler; stir over medium heat until smooth.
Add noodles and toss lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's garden club corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar on low speed for 15 minutes.
Fold in flour and salt.
Add lemon juice or vanilla if desired.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Crush crackers; add sugar and butter. Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Reserve some mixture for topping.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine, but do not mix in blender.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: the mess
directions: Put oleo in large pan.
Cut up all vegetables except tomatoes. Cook until nearly tender, turn off heat.
Cook kolbassi separately and add to vegetables.
When ready to eat, heat up and add tomatoes.

title: caribbean dumplings
directions: Sift flour; stir in salt and beaten eggs.
Gradually stir in the sour cream and let stand 2 hours.
Stir in melted butter and the baking soda, dissolved in the tablespoon of water.
Drop batter from a teaspoon into hot, deep fat at 380° and fry until golden. Drain on paper towel.

title: enchilada chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine, chicken, soups and salsa. Cut tortillas into quarters. Spray 9x12-inch casserole dish with cooking spray. Line bottom of casserole dish with tortillas, covering the bottom. Layer with 1/2 chicken mixture. Add one more layer of tortillas. Add one more layer of chicken mixture. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Serve cool.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Put chicken broth in pot with diced celery, pepper, parsley and egg noodles (break up some).
Cook for 1 1/4 hours.
Add cooked chicken and can of creamed corn and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour into oiled 1-quart ring mold or individual molds and chill until firm.
May also be made in 8-inch square pan and cut in squares.
Nice with cottage cheese or tuna salad.

title: mix 'n match squash casserole
directions: Place squash and a small amount of water in a large saucepan; cover and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
(You may also microwave until tender.)
Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Transfer to a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix on high speed 2 minutes all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured Bundt pan for 50 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 16.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 8 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup whipped topping and spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth and thick.
Let stand 1 hour. Spread over cheese layer.
Spread remaining whipped topping over all and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit together.
Sprinkle 1 small package of instant pudding mix over fruit with pineapple juice.
This makes a sauce. (NutraSweet instant pudding is good over this.)

title: "never fail"  skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in iron skillet.
Beat egg yolks; add to milk.
Mix this with dry mix.
Cook over medium to low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Microwave for 2 minutes on Full power.
Stir and add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and stir.
Pour into greased square dish and put into refrigerator for 30 minutes before cutting in squares and serving.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to a boil; stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until all the water is absorbed.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and lettuce. Cut in pieces and place in bowl with diced onion. Cook bacon and let cool. Crumble into lettuce and cauliflower.

title: easy cake mix cookie recipe
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Roll in ball and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
(May add nuts or chocolate chips to cookie mixture if desired.)

title: champagne dessert
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, add drained pineapple tidbits, strawberries, walnuts, bananas and whipped topping.
Mix gently, but thoroughly.
Combine with cream cheese mixture and spoon in an oversized loaf pan.
Freeze until solid.
To serve, cut into slices.

title: barbeque pork
directions: Boil the Boston butt for 3 to 5 hours
in salted water. Cool and remove from juice. Skim off most of the fat, leaving enough for flavor. Break meat into medium pieces and set aside.

title: mock duck
directions: Saute celery and onions in oleo until tender.
Pour over croutettes, bread, salt and pepper.
Mix together in large mixing bowl.
Stir in hot water to moisten.

title: banana split snack cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in the egg, banana and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to the creamed mixture. Add walnuts.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients.
Batter is thick but runny.
Fry in deep fryer in Crisco oil.
Make sure oil is hot.
When fritter floats to top and is golden brown on all sides, it's done.

title: joyce's dressing
directions: Boil hen and save broth.
Debone hen and mix with boiled vegetables.
Boil diced onions and celery in 2 cups water until tender, then mix with other ingredients.
Mix everything together and leave real juicy.
(Add more broth, if needed.)
Bake at 375° until firm.

title: american cheese lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package.
Brown ground beef; add diced onion and green pepper to meat.
Heat tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce in a saucepan.
Add meat mixture.
Simmer while noodles cook.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish, layer noodles, sauce mixture and American cheese, broken into 1/2-inch strips and Parmesan cheese.
Top this with another layer of noodles, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until cheese bubbles.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Form into 8 patties and fry in small amount of vegetable shortening until brown.

title: make ahead mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground meat and onion until lightly browned, stirring to crumble the meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Alternate meat mixture and tortillas, beginning and ending with the meat mixture in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
tags: cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll in 1-inch balls.
Cool while you melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Stick a toothpick in balls and dip in chocolate mixture.

title: kate thomas' potato pancakes(kartoffel plannkuchen)
directions: Drain off excess water from potatoes.
Add flour, grated onion, garlic, eggs and salt.
Mix and drop by tablespoonful into heated vegetable oil.
Fry until golden crisp on one side, turn over and fry on other side.
Serves 4.

title: janet's slush(serves 12)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large Tupperware container.
Taste and add sugar as needed.
Freeze.
Take out about 1 hour before serving time.
Use a large cooking spoon and break up into chunks.
Serve as a refreshing summer treat.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Beat Bisquick, milk, eggs and salt until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake until knife inserted in middle comes out clean (about 1 hour).
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: hoagie dip
directions: Slice Italian bread in one-inch slices. Layer meat and cheese, one on top of the other.
Roll up tight and then slice into pinwheels not quite an inch wide.
Take a large bowl and tear up half a head of lettuce.
Cut up tomatoes into cubes.
Dice small onion.
Put your meat and cheese pinwheels in with 1 tablespoon mayonnaise, little oil, oregano and Italian seasoning.
Toss and serve with spoon on slices of Italian bread.

title: sweet & sour dressing
directions: Blend together in blender then refrigerate.

title: sliced tomatoes
directions: Place a layer of sliced, unpeeled tomatoes in a shallow bowl. Place a thin slice of onion on each tomato slice.
Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper and a pinch of basil. Sprinkle on 1/2 teaspoon sugar, 1 teaspoon vinegar and a little olive oil.
Keep layering until you have what you need.

title: lemon-angel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray jelly roll pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Spread on pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
When cool, you can sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: ever easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Grease two 9 x 5 loaf pans. Combine flour and soda; set aside. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend in dry ingredients. Pour half of the ingredients into each pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 - 25 minutes. Cool 15 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in skillet (drain).
Stir in onion, bell pepper, sauce, mushrooms.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Meanwhile cook noodles. Layer noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese in shallow rectangular baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes.

title: bean and tomato casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to directions on package.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Add tomato and bacon; simmer an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
Place beans and tomato mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, oil, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Add oats, flakes and peanuts; stir well.
Add flour. Drop by
small
spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until
slightly
brown.
Bake
15 minutes.
Yields 5 or 6 dozen. Cool before removing from sheet.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and add vinegar and oil.
Mix well and add catsup and celery seed.
You can also add a little grated onions or a little garlic powder.

title: carrot-cheddar casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water.
Drain and stir oleo into carrots.
Mash coarsely with a fork.
Combine rest of ingredients and put into a casserole.
Bake at 325° until knife comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate delight
directions: In ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer nuts and coconut. Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Pour over top of cake batter. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add milk, pineapple and cottage cheese; mix well.
Add other ingredients and congeal.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray
9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick coating.
Sprinkle chopped pecans and coconut into bottom.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour over pecans and coconut. Beat together cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and sugar.
Spoon mixture on top of cake batter.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cake will crack open when done, but test for doneness.

title: wieners
directions: Simmer the 3 above ingredients for 2 hours.
When cooked, cut wieners in half and put toothpick in each half.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in an angel food cake tube pan at 350° for 1 hr. or until done.

title: broken peanut brittle cake
directions: Beat
eggs,
sugar
and
half of cake mix until smooth. Mix in other half of mix and the peanuts.
Press 1/3 of stiff dough onto a cookie sheet.
Repeat on two others.
Use fingers to press into rectangles of about 13 x 8-inches.	Bake at 375° for
to
10 minutes.
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes and remove from
baking pans with spatula.
Break into pieces like peanut brittle.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Put 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, milk and butter on stove.
After cake is done, sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over hot cake.
Then pour caramel mixture over this.
Pour rest of cake batter over this.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: angelic enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breast until done and chop into pieces.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Mix well and add apples and nuts.
Bake at 275° for approximately 1 1/2 hours in a waxed paper-lined tube pan.

title: brisket
directions: Place beef brisket in baking dish.
Sprinkle garlic salt and celery seed on brisket.
Cover with liquid smoke.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust and chill until set, 3 to 4 hours.
Serve plain or with canned pie fillings or fresh strawberries.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Put marshmallows in a large bowl.
Add fruit cocktail, pecans and sour cream.
Mix well together.
Let stay at room temperature for 45 minutes.
Chill.

title: pineapple pistachio salad
directions: Mix everything together (pudding to be dry).
Chill overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Add onion, garlic salt, pepper. Cook for 5 more minutes.
Turn burner down to lowest setting and add remaining ingredients. Stir constantly to prevent scorching.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo, then mix all ingredients except pecans.
In double boiler, heat until sugar and butter blend.
Pour in pecans and mix well.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: crazy gravy chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, 1/2 cup sherry wine and diced onions in a bowl.
Cover all chicken parts with mixture.
Top with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
(Cheese makes a delightful brown topping on chicken.)

title: quick cinnamon bites
directions: Mix cinnamon with sugar.
Divide each biscuit into 4 parts. Roll each part in mixture and line bottom of greased pan with them.
Put dabs of butter on top of each piece and top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat cream, water and margarine until margarine is melted. Add cheese and parsley.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serves 6.
A very delicious and moist dish.

title: orange coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add everything else.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Real good!
Serves 8.

title: fish-potato soup(psarosoupa)
directions: Saute onions, celery and carrots in oil until soft.
Add potatoes, seasonings, water, tomatoes and fish (cut into 3-inch pieces).
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream and grated cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Add sour cream and grated cheese.
Bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: holiday fruit balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll up in small balls, then roll in coconut.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: In a blender, blend together at high speed garlic, anchovies, lemon juice, mayonnaise and salt until smooth.
Add olive oil by steady stream at lower speed to blend.
Add portion of dressing to romaine lettuce and toss until well coated.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown onions and chuck in skillet.
Line casserole with Tater Tots.
Top with meat mixture.
Combine soups and add to casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg and cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fry chik casserole(i use this in place of turkey on holidays)
directions: In a large bowl, pour hot milk over croutons and chopped butter and stir.
Scramble eggs and add all ingredients; mix well. Turn mixture into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan or equal size and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Vegetarian Gravy.

title: herb green beans
directions: Cook green beans in boiling water. While beans are cooking, melt butter and add onions. Cook 5 minutes.
Add garlic salt, parsley, rosemary, basil and salt. Simmer 10 minutes. Drain beans and toss with herb flavored butter.

title: silver turtles
directions: Build a charcoal base.
Put patties of chopped ground beef in double thick aluminum foil.
Add vegetables.
Roll foil to achieve a vapor tight seal.
Cook for 20 minutes on first side, then 20 minutes on second side.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Fry like pancakes in vegetable oil until brown.

title: four layer chocolate dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix butter, flour and 1 cup nuts and spread in a large Pyrex dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: crab puffs
directions: Partially drain the crab meat.
Mix with cream cheese and Tabasco sauce.
Salt to taste.

title: special zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini, carrots and onions until tender.
Drain well. Add soup and sour cream.
Layer, in greased casserole, vegetables and crushed croutons, ending with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: super waffles
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Gradually add milk, stirring well.
Add egg yolks and melted butter.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold into mixture. Bake in waffle iron.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix fruit.
Add pineapple juice and 1 box vanilla instant pudding together and mix well.
Combine with fruit.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Thaw broccoli; drain and place in a baking dish.
Melt oleo and combine with flour, salt and milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Place cheese slices on top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Stir and let set for a few minutes.

title: church chicken
directions: May use turkey, too!
tags: cream of celery soup or mushroom soup

title: spicy sausage-bean soup
directions: Brown sausage in a large Dutch oven, stirring to crumble meat. Drain off pan drippings. Stir in all other ingredients, except last two. Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add green pepper and potatoes; cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: red beans and sausage with rice
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven. Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours. Drain.
Cover beans with water and add ham hock; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: bread dip
directions: Cut ham into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and add ham.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted margarine and sugar and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and put on top of pretzels. Combine strawberry jello, boiling water and strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese and chill overnight.

title: northern pigs and blanket
directions: Peel steamed cabbage leaves (set aside). Mix hamburger, egg, onion, rice, salt and pepper. Roll in cabbage leaves. Put sauerkraut, water and caraway seeds in a roasting pan (cover). Put your wrapped hamburger on top of sauerkraut and bake in a 350° oven for about 3 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tossed fettucine
directions: Drain and flake chicken or ham.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until soft.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, yogurt, cheese, pepper, fettucine and peas.
Mix well.
Add chicken and ham; toss lightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In large iron skillet, melt butter and saute onion, garlic, celery, turnip, potatoes, tomato and cabbage.
Add salt, pepper and parsley to taste.
To sauteed ingredients, add frozen vegetables.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add frozen okra and cook another 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour beef broth into large soup pot along with tomato sauce.
Heat and add vegetable mixture.
Add sugar and simmer for 1 hour.
Add macaroni or rice and simmer 30 minutes.

title: lisa's pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and add 1 cup each of the following fruits: strawberries, blueberries, peaches, red grapes, bananas and cherries.
Put into a pie crust (any kind you like) and chill.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except parsley and nuts).
Form into ball.
Roll in parsley and nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: ice cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and cornstarch until thickened.
Cool and set aside. Whip shortening and gradually add sugar a little at a time until all sugar is added.
Add milk and cornstarch; mix, add vanilla and keep whipping until sugar is dissolved.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In skillet, cook pork sausage, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion and peppers are tender.
Drain off fat; set aside. In bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions.
Cool and crumble into a large bowl.
Add chopped onion, pepper and tomatoes.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Add bacon and mix.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Steam shrimp about 1 minute.
Set aside and peel when cool. Don't steam too long because you're gonna use them in the hot sauce later on.
Nobody likes to eat soggy shrimp.

title: aunt tillie's strawberry dessert
directions: Combine flour and margarine as for pie dough.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Bake
at
for	20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool immediately.
This part can be done the day before. Then
beat
together
the	cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip
and
place
on
top of the cooled crust. Chill
while preparing
the
following:	Mix together Jell-O, sugar and cornstarch in medium-sized saucepan.
Add hot water. Bring to
a full
boil.
Boil
1 minute, stirring constantly. Cool thoroughly. Fold
in sliced fresh strawberries and place on top of
Cool Whip
mixture.
Keep
chilled
until ready to serve.

title: piquant squash
directions: Place skillet on medium heat and add oil.
Lightly cook/brown the onion and add squash, green pepper and garlic.
Stir quickly and reduce heat to medium.
Add the corn, tomato, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir well and within 5 minutes, turn stove off.
Let the mixture stand for 5 minutes more and then serve.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Bring salted water to a boil.
Add grits gradually.
Reduce heat and cook until mixture becomes thick, stirring frequently, about 20 or 30 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the cheese, butter and Worcestershire sauce while hot and set aside.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.

title: huckleberry dessert
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Alternately add flour and milk.
Grease bottom of 9-inch baking dish.
Line with berries.
Pour batter over berries.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes until golden brown and cake tester comes out clean.
Serve cut in squares.

title: baked hash brown supreme
directions: Pour half the melted oleo over the thawed potatoes, then mix in soup, sour cream, onion and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in greased baking dish and cover with remaining cheese.
Combine remaining oleo with bread crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix the 3 soups and milk together in a large saucepan.
Add the mushrooms, if desired, undrained.
Heat until well blended. Do not burn!
The broccoli does better if precooked to crisp, either on the stove or microwave.
Add to the hot soup mixture. The cheese is added last.
Stir until melted into the soup.
You can use other vegetables (cauliflower, asparagus or a combination).
Other cheeses can be used also (Swiss, Cheddar). You really can't ruin this.
I have even added leftover cooked ham to it.

title: cow cookies
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat to 350°.
Grease baking sheet and dust with flour.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Using electric mixer, cream margarine with both sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until light and fluffy.
Mix in milk and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients into batter.
Fold in oats, chocolate chips and walnuts.
Using 1/3 cup for each cookie, drop batter onto prepared sheets, spacing 3 inches apart.
Bake until cookies are light brown around the edges for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 3 minutes.

title: reo beans and rice
directions: Wash Reo beans thoroughly and put in large pot filled with hot water.
Cook for 3 to 4 hours on high (until tender).
You may need to add more water while cooking.
After the beans are tender, add Accent, salt, pepper and butter.
Then add the slices of smoked sausage.
Let cook on medium for another hour.

title: bisquick banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan well.
Beat all ingredients 30 seconds with spoon.
Pour in pan and bake for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature.
Add onion juice and Worcestershire and blend on low speed in blender until creamy. Cover and chill.
Shape mixture into large ball.
Roll in parsley flakes.
Decorate with olives, pimento, etc.
(Can also make into little individual balls.)

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: In blender container, puree strawberries. In pitcher, combine pureed strawberries, water, lemon juice and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add club soda.
Serve over ice and garnish with strawberries and/or mint leaves.
Yields 4 servings.

title: green beans and water chestnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onion rings.
Put in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed
onion rings on top. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo to soft ball stage.
Pour half of this over beaten egg whites.
Boil rest to hard ball stage.
Pour over egg whites and beat well.
It is ready when holds shape.
(If don't have candy thermometer, cook until spins thread and add it all at one time.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Sprinkle orange jello over cottage cheese.
Add pineapple, oranges and the Cool Whip all together.
Chill thoroughly.

title: macaroni and shrimp casserole
directions: Boil macaroni.
Saute shallots in butter; then add shrimp. Saute 15 minutes longer.
Add soup and cook until thick.
Add macaroni and cheese packet; mix well.
Pour into a baking dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: dolly beck's fudge dainties
directions: Beat together the eggs and sugar.
Melt together over low heat, or use double boiler, the butter and baking chocolate.
Add to egg mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch glass baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or slightly longer if needed.
These brownies are moist and chewy.

title: rabes
directions: Cut stems, and wash rabes; drain.
Heat garlic, olive oil and red pepper for about 1 minute on medium heat.
(Do not burn garlic.)
Add rabes to oil; cover.
Add a little water;
stir rabes every few minutes.
When they are tender, add white wine. Remove cover and let cook just a few more minutes.

title: hot mocha mix(spiced)
directions: Mix
in
container
with
lid.	Store in dry place.
To mix, add 2 heaping tablespoonfuls to 1 cup boiling water.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add enchilada sauce, olives, beans, tomato sauce and garlic.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Line bottom of casserole with tortillas. Add part of enchilada mixture, then a layer of cheese, then another layer of tortillas, enchilada sauce and layer of cheese on top.
Place in oven and let bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: super simple cheesecake
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together well.
Add Cool Whip. When well blended, put in graham cracker pie crust and chill.
Top with pie filling and serve.
Kids love it!

title: sugar sour cream nuts
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix sugar, sour cream and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly to 236°.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Add nuts and stir quickly to coat all sides.
Turn out onto greased cookie sheet and separate nuts with 2 forks.

title: tea time tassties
directions: Pastry:
Soften cheese and butter at room temperature.
Stir in flour.
Chill about 1 hour. Shape into 2 dozen balls.
Place in tiny ungreased muffin pans.
Press dough on bottom and sides.

title: carrot bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: honey corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in liquid ingredients.
Stir in corn.
Do not overmix!
Corn bread batter must be a little lumpy.
Pour batter into well buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 1/2 hour without corn or 55 minutes with corn until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool slightly and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: dilled chicken fricassee
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika; coat chicken.
Reserve leftover flour mixture.
Heat oil in a deep 12-inch skillet.
Add chicken and brown.
Stir reserved flour mixture into pan drippings. Gradually stir in chicken broth, then 2 tablespoons dill; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add green beans; cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until chicken and potatoes are tender and beans are crisp-tender.
Stir in lemon juice and sprinkle with remaining dill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Beat egg, milk and hot pepper sauce in a shallow bowl.
Combine bread crumbs with salt and pepper in a pan.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Dip tomato slices in the mild mixture, shaking off any excess, then lightly coat with crumbs.
Fry a few slices at a time until golden, about 2 minutes on each side.
Fry remaining tomato slices, adding more butter to skillet as needed. Drain on paper towel.

title: drop candies
directions: Mix first ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Let stay in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cover greased pan with rolls to form a crust and pinch together.
Brown and drain sausage; place on crust.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over sausage.
Bake until firm, about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown flour.
Add rest of ingredients in order, then cover with water.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into long rectangles. Place rolls in ungreased pan.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides.
Seal perforations.
Bake for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Blend sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spread evenly over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into appetizer size.
Store in refrigerator.

title: microwave sweet corn
directions: Place water, sugar, then corn in microwave-safe casserole dish in single layer.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into bowl.
Mix together with fork or pastry blender.
Then stir just until blended.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: all-bran rolls
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, bran and salt.
Add boiling water; stir until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast that has been dissolved in lukewarm water.
Add 3 cups flour; beat well.
Add remaining flour and beat well.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Shape into rolls (or can roll up and cut out like biscuits); allow to rise again.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball spread
directions: Mix all together, shape into ball and roll into crushed walnuts.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or breadsticks.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken, onions
and
celery about 1 hour.
Debone chicken and chop.
Return
to
broth.
Add	the
extra cans of chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Add pepper and seasoned salt. Add egg noodles and cook according to package.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Add soup, water and rice in cake pan.
Cook over low heat until all blended together.
Clean and put pieces of chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup over top of chicken and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until done, around 75 minutes, covered. Then uncover for 30 minutes to brown.

title: eggplant sauce
directions: Fry eggplant, onion and garlic together.
When lightly browned, add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: microwave brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef
and
sausage and drain.
Drain corn. Combine all ingredients and microwave for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda. Set aside. Mix margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto baking pan.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: bucket of dirt
directions: Crumble cookies fine.
After preparing pudding, let set, then mix with Cool Whip and softened cream cheese.
Purchase a ceramic flower pot or plastic pail.
Put cookie crumbs in the bottom of the pot or pail.
On top, add a layer of pudding mixture, then crumbs, then pudding, etc., ending with crumbs on top.

title: saucy pizza
directions: Split and toast muffin halves; spread pizza sauce on halves and top with cheese and topping of choice.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 pizzas.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Blend sour cream, chopped onion, cumin and 1 cup of the cheese.
Fry tortillas in the oil and dip into the heated enchilada sauce.
In an ungreased casserole, about 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch, overlap two tortillas at one end of the pan, allowing part of the tortillas to extend over the edge of the pan.

Spread about 6 tablespoons of the sour cream filling down the center of the tortillas; fold the extending section down over the filling. Repeat this process to fill remaining tortillas, placing them side by side and completely covering pan bottom; use all the filling. Sprinkle remaining 3 cups of cheese evenly over the top.
(You can cover and chill the casserole for several hours if you want to make it ahead.)
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 375°.
Garnish with more sour cream spooned down the center; sprinkle with more chopped green onion.
Makes 6 large enchiladas.

title: apple salad bowl
directions: Wash, core out and cut apples into small wedges.
Section oranges.
Toss both apples and oranges with peanuts, onion
and cabbage in salad bowl.
Before serving, toss with the French dressing.

title: cheesy dip
directions: Melt butter with chopped onion.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add hot sauces; stir until smooth.
Pour into serving dish.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add green onions and package of taco seasoning.
Cook as package directs.
Add green onions after beef is brown.
Put foil on cookie sheet.
Layer the shells, sauce, ground beef mixture and cheese.
Layer until ingredients are all used.
Put tent of foil on pie when baking.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Garnish with sour cream, if desired.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: In a bowl combine egg, milk, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add meat and cooked rice.
Mix well.

title: spiced oat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
In small bowl combine flour, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
In mixing bowl with electric mixer at high beat butter and brown sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute.
Stir in squash puree.
Gradually stir in flour mixture, oats and raisins until combined.
Drop dough by 1/4 cupfuls onto baking sheets.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until brown. Cool on wire rack.
Cool 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well. Store in plastic container or airtight tin.
Fill cup 1/3 to 1/2 full with mix and add boiling water.
Keeps indefinitely.
Makes enough to fill two small coffee cans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first
4 ingredients and half the ham.
Roll into a ball. Take
remaining
ham
and cover cheese ball.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: microwave salmon dumplings
directions: Combine salmon, soup, milk, flour, green pepper and parsley. Arrange biscuits over bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon salmon mixture over biscuits.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes, spooning sauce over biscuits once during cooking.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salt cod with cabbage
directions: Soak 1 lb of salt cod in cold water to cover, changing the water several times, for 24 hours and then drain the fish.
Remove any skin and bones, dry fish with a paper towel.
Cut into 2 inch pieces.
In a large skillet saute onion, red pepper, garlic and parsley in olive oil until the onion is softened.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, white wine, the cod and pepper.
Combine mixture and simmer it partially covered for 10-15 minutes or until the cabbage is tender and the cod flakes easily when tested with a fork. (Serves 4.)

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill about 1 hour.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick. Cut into strips. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: the smokey mountains
directions: Toast and brush lightly each muffin half with garlic butter. Spread 2 teaspoons dressing on each.
Top each with half slices of bacon, 1 ounce pastrami, 1/2 ounce ham and 1/2 slice cheese. Place 2 pickle slices crisscross over cheese.
Broil until cheese begins to melt.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate leftover pie.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together; cover and refrigerate.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into bite size meatballs.

title: butter crust
directions: Combine butter with sugar; do not cream.
Add flour.
Mix until dough will form.
Remove 1/4 cup for crumbs for topping. Press remaining dough into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375°, crust for 12 to 15 minutes, crumbs for 10 to 12 minutes.
Good crust for frozen pies.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into small 3/4-inch meatballs.
Arrange in shallow 15 x 10-inch pan or several smaller pans.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add bananas and continue beating.
Add milk, beat then add flour.
Beat and fold in nuts.
Bake in 325° oven in a greased and floured loaf pan for 45 minutes.
This recipe is so good that you will want to double it and perhaps divide into about 3 mini-loaves to share with others.
It still takes from 35 to 45 minutes to bake small loaves, depending upon your oven.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients three times.
Make well and put in mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Mix until batter is smooth.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Beat all ingredients (but carrots and pecans) in bowl on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium 3 minutes. Stir in carrots and pecans. Pour in pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: my mom's easy caramel rolls
directions: Put raisins into boiling water and baking soda; let stand to cool.

Mix sugar, egg and salt together; cream for 2 minutes. Pour water mixture into sugar and eggs; turn speed to very low. Add flour and baking powder at one time; consistency is thick. Mix until flour is blended, then add nuts.
Pour into 2 small greased loaf tins.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes to cool and take out of pan.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Go to Food Lion and buy a dead turkey.
Cook it in the oven however long you want to.
Take it out of the oven and slice it up.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook beef and onion until done.
Drain and stir in taco seasoning.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch baking dish and sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender for a few seconds.
Pour mixture into a 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: gaslight explosion
directions: Mix together.
Guaranteed to put a shine in Irish eyes!

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, flour and salt in dry bowl or pan.
Mix water and lemon juice together and add to mixture.
Add pie fruit. Fold gently.
Measure approximately 1 quart per unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust or lattice top and bake about 40 minutes at 400°.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave butter in 4-quart bowl on High until melted.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until boiling, stirring every 3 minutes.
Microwave only 3 minutes more.
Stir in 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave; add other ingredients.
Stir until melted.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour and refrigerate until set, about 2 1/2 hours.
Yield: 3 pounds.

title: meat-potato quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Put the raw potato in the pan; press evenly into pan.
Spray again with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, until beginning to brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour and then stir. Bake for another 1/2 hour.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble and drain.
Saute onion and garlic in bacon drippings.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour hot over hot vegetables or torn greens.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve at once.
Serves 4. Makes 1/2 cup.
Two tablespoons contains 52 calories.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Into standard measuring cup, break the egg, beat lightly and fill the cup with milk.
Add to dry ingredients, beat a little and let stand to raise for 5 minutes.

title: turkey taco salad*
directions: Brown turkey with seasonings.
Cool.
Make salad with lettuce and tomatoes (may add green onions, etc.).
Add cheese and mix well.
Do not add chips until ready to serve so they will stay crisp.

title: basic refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Combine margarine, sugar, boiling water and salt; stir until lukewarm. Add egg, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture; beat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour; knead.
Place dough in a greased bowl.
Grease top of dough.
Refrigerate.
When ready to use, put dough in a warm place for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Pour in strawberries.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Put angel food pieces in Jell-O.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Put on Cool Whip; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: world famous wine punch
directions: Put strawberries in bowl with sugar and 1 bottle wine.
Let blend 3 hours.
Beat this mixture in a blender until pureed. Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl and serve.

title: baked fresh catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash catfish in cold running water and drain well.
Place in a large bowl and add mayonnaise and cover both sides of each fish.
(Mayonnaise should be thick on the fish.)
Mix well the flour, cornmeal and salt.
Coat both sides and inside the cavity of the catfish with the cornmeal mixture (it will be thick).
Carefully place fish apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn carefully each fish and cook for 20 more minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves four.

title: hawaiian banana pineapple bread
directions: Combine the dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine the other ingredients to the flour and add raisins.
Bake in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured or sprayed with Pam, for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes. Frost with Caramel Icing.

title: ambrosia jello salad
directions: Stir boiling water and Jell-O until dissolved.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add cold water juice to make one cup.
Mix Jell-O and pineapple mixtures.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Then stir in remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad supreme
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Add salt, drain and rinse thoroughly.
Add Miracle Whip, mustard, green peppers, sweet pickles, tomatoes, celery, onions and cheese.
A little pickle juice and possibly a pinch of sugar may be added.
Mix and stir all these ingredients well.
Place in salad bowl and sprinkle top with paprika.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix salt in water; pour over sliced cucumbers and onions.
Let set 3 to 4 hours.
Bring sugar, spices, cornstarch and vinegar to a boil.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Add cucumbers and onions (drained).
Heat thoroughly.
Pack in sterile jars while hot and seal.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine and bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in large grocery bag and set aside.
Combine sugar, margarine, syrup, vanilla and salt.
Microwave on High 4 minutes. Stir after 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; mix.
Pour over popcorn and stir to combine.
Place bag in microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag to stir popcorn.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour on waxed paper or cookie sheets to cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In round 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish, combine corn syrup and sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Microwave on High (100%) power for 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Microwave on High power 4 to 6 minutes or until light brown. Stir in butter and vanilla, blending well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes. Add baking soda and stir gently just until light and foamy. Quickly pour onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Cool.
Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: broccoli ham and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place mixture in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Lightly grease or spray baking dish with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with chicken and then vegetables.
Mix together soups and pepper and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix together melted margarine, Bisquick and milk and pour over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° until golden brown.

title: italian baked onions
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cut onions in half, crosswise. Trim ends so they stand flat.
Scoop out centers and reserve. Pour 1 tbsp. olive oil into baking dish.
Add onions, turn to coat.
Arrange cut sides up, drizzle with vinegar.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until tender.
Mince reserved onion, mix with remaining ingredients.
Mound in the centers and bake uncovered 20 minutes or until golden.
Serves 4.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add crumbled yeast cake.
Melt shortening, along with salt, 1/2 of the milk and all of the sugar over low heat.
Add rest of the milk.
While mixture is yet lukewarm, add to egg white mixture.
Mix in the flour.
Let set 1 hour.
Form into small balls; place on greased baking sheet for 1 hour.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt all ingredients.
Pour over 1 (12 ounce) package Kellogg's Crispix cereal and stir well.
Place in a large plastic bag and add 3 cups powdered sugar.
Shake to coat.
Store in freezer.

title: chicken wing marinade
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over chicken wings.
Marinate at least 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: bulk brownie mix
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put in gallon jar or container with lid.

title: macaroni and hot dogs
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Slice hot dogs and warm.
Warm drained peas.
Combine all together.

title: ice cream cake 1
directions: Take ice cream out and let soften.
Mix crushed Oreos with melted butter.
Press into the bottom of a 12-inch round plastic container (like Tupperware pie-taker with lid).
Spread ice cream over cookies.
Pour fudge evenly over ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip over fudge.
Garnish with more crushed Oreos, if desired, or freeze and decorate as for a birthday.
Re-freeze for 24 hours, but remove to allow softening before cutting.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Pour 7-Up and Verners over frozen grape juice.
Mix.
Decorate with lime slices.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and jello.
Add hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add juice from pineapple and let gel slightly. Add crushed pineapple, carrots and Cool Whip.
Pour into a mold and chill until firm.

title: shirley's pan cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple together in cake pan. Pour cake mix over filling.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls and bake at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes or lightly brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, tossing well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: party  cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and (optional) cheddar cheese until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients except pecans.
Shape in balls and roll the balls in pecans. Chills. Makes about three cups.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a salad bowl, then mix the following dressing:

title: lemon fluff pudding
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup of the sugar and flour in mixing bowl. Add egg yolks; beat well.
Stir in lemon rind, juice and milk.
In a different bowl, add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff. Slowly add in remaining 1/2 cup of sugar; fold into first mixture. Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Set dish in shallow pan, containing boiling water 1-inch deep.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Cool.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash seasoned with salt and pepper.
Add other ingredients (can be put in blender) except herb dressing.
Melt butter and mix with dressing.
Add half of dressing-butter mixture to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and cover top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble cooked hamburg in bottom of 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Mix soup with milk and pour over hamburg and onion.
Next, put on a layer of cheese and top with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: green pea picnic salad
directions: Place peas in a colander and run cool water over them to thaw.
Set aside to drain well.
Cut the cucumber in half and using a spoon, scrape out the seeds.
Chop the cucumber and place it in a 2-quart or larger bowl.
Peel and finely mince the garlic, adding it to the bowl.
Add basil, red bell pepper and onion.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon, salt and pepper to the bowl.
Stir well to mix the vegetables.
Add the green peas and toss to coat. Mix well.
Serve at once or cover and chill up to 24 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute celery.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add topping.

title: buster bar
directions: Combine crushed oreos and margarine.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13 inch dish or pan.
Freeze until firm, about 30 minutes. Next, spread softened ice cream.
Sprinkle and press into ice cream 1/2 cup of the nuts.
Freeze at least 2 hours.

title: no-bake cake
directions: Break
cake
in
small pieces.	Mix with pineapple. Add pudding and stir.
Pour into large bowl. Cover with Cool Whip. Chill and serve cold.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Add oleo; mix and put in casserole pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Simmer gently the butter, onions and cut up potatoes.
When tender, add clams and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Bring everything to a boil and thicken slightly with cornstarch mixture.
This is one of our traditional foods on Christmas Eve.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In a large pot, add the stock and barley and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add to the stock the carrots, celery and onions.
Mix together and let this simmer for another 1/2 hour.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Combine and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, paprika and parsley.

title: lemon cream for fruit
directions: Add vanilla and let cool.
Fold in whipping cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: sugared pecan halves
directions: Place pecan halves in 15 x 10-inch pan and bake in a 325° oven for about 10 minutes until lightly browned. Remove from pan and cool.
Place butter in pan and melt.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Fold nuts into mixture and put back into pan. Separate nuts carefully and return to 325° oven for 30 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes until all butter is absorbed. Cool and store.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn meal and nutmeg.
Mix well; add margarine.
Bake in 350° oven in pie shell until done.

title: braccioli(beef rolls)
directions: Have top round cut into thin slices and flattened.
Cut slices to desired widths.
Cover slices with mixture of cheese, finely chopped parsley and garlic, raisins, salt and pepper.
Roll each braccioli and secure rolls with toothpicks.
Brown the rolled meat and finely chopped onion in oil.

title: easy pork chop meal
directions: In large skillet, put in oil.
Lay pork chops in.
Put seasoning on chops.
Lay potatoes, cut into 4 quarters, carrot sticks and onion quarters on top.
Cover tightly and cook 15 minutes.
Turn pork chops.
Replace lid.
Cook on low until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Place strawberries in bowl and sprinkle jello over.
Mix.
In a separate bowl mix sour cream, Cool Whip and pudding (already mixed with milk).
Then layer 1/2 wafers, berries and pudding, then wafers, berries and pudding.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate oatsies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add rest of ingredients and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yields 30 cookies.
Great for hot days (no oven).

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken wings.
Marinate chicken wings in sauce for 48 hours.
Stir occasionally.
To bake, spread on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: endive salad
directions: Wash and chop endive. Chop bacon and fry until crisp. Cool slightly. Add water and vinegar to bacon drippings and pour over endive and chopped onion to which sugar, salt and pepper have been added. Serves 4 to 6.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Bring mixture to a boil.
Cool and pour over cabbage mixture. Mix well, put in jars and keep in refrigerator.
Will keep well for weeks.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Melt butter.
Have sour cream at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spray muffin pan.
Will make 12
muffin biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Blend all ingredients well, reserving milk for last.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, lowering oven temperature to 300° for another 30 minutes.

title: no-sugar cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients together with a wooden spoon.
Drop with spoon onto cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil 1 quart water and sugar in a large container, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, save ice until last.
Serves about 100.

title: drumsticks parmesan
directions: Combine herb stuffing, Parmesan cheese, parsley and garlic. Dip drumsticks in melted butter and roll in crumb mixture.
Place pieces, skin side up and not touching, in greased jellyroll pan. Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° about 1 hour or until done.
Do not turn.

title: black-eyed pea corn bread
directions: Brown the meat and drain well.
Break into small pieces.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been well-greased.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 10 to 12 servings (probably more by using smaller pieces; served at Black History month luncheon.)

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Mix oranges, green pepper, seasonings and pineapple with juice.
Add chicken.
Pour into baking dish and bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel nut slices
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, salt and soda together.
Add to sugar mixture; form into rolls and chill overnight.
Slice and bake at 400°.

title: jam and cheese loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in biscuit mix, egg and 1 tablespoon sugar; mix well.
Turn onto biscuit mix-dusted surface. Knead 20 times.
Place on center of greased 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheet.
Roll to a 14 x 9-inch rectangle.

title: best ever baked beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion, salt and pepper in pan.
In bowl, combine the three cans of beans.
Blend in the brown sugar, catsup, mustard, barbecue sauce and vinegar.
Gently stir in browned onion and bacon.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, depending on how dry you like your beans.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
In saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well and pour in greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. (If using
9 x 13-inch pan, allow extra baking time.)

title: the duchess of windsor's popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix and sift flour and salt; add milk gradually. Mix until batter is smooth. Add eggs. Add melted butter. Beat mixture for 2 minutes with rotary beater. Grease muffin tins and place in hot oven until hot. Remove tins from oven and pour batter into tins, filling 2/3 full. Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes longer, until brown and popped up! Do not open oven door during baking. Yield:
8 muffins. This recipe can be doubled.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add sugar and cocoa; mix until well blended. Add eggs, then evaporated milk and vanilla.
Stir well. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; turn oven down to 350° and bake for an additional 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy lemon bars
directions: Stir together the angel food cake mix and the can of lemon pie filling.
(Do not use a mixer.)
Pour into a greased pan.
If the pan is a jelly roll pan, bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
If the pan is a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Frost with your choice of canned frosting.

title: cheese balls
directions: Save 1 cup pecans for rolling.
Combine remaining ingredients. Chill before rolling into 2 balls.

title: easy crumb cake
directions: Mix margarine, cinnamon and sugars until crumbles.
Bake cake in foil pan (sheet cake style).
Ten minutes before done, sprinkle on crumb mixture.
Bake additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, eggs and granulated sugar together.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and add to cocktail.
Mix and pour batter into greased pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and coconut over batter.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Leave in pan.

title: cooked apples
directions: Put apples, bacon grease and water in skillet (do not use an iron skillet).
Cook down a little.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until done.

title: fruit cup salad
directions: Combine all fruits, then combine and blend remaining ingredients.
Serve salad on crisp lettuce leaf.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs.
Sift and add dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in 3 greased and floured round 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Start heating oven to 350° and grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
With electric mixer at medium speed or with spoon, thoroughly mix shortening with sugar, then with egg yolks until very light and fluffy, about 4 minutes altogether.
Then, at low speed, beat in flour mixture alternately with bananas just until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn mixture into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove.
Cool overnight before slicing.

title: yummy taters
directions: In a paper bag, mix the breading mix, flour, cheese and salt. Put the washed potatoes into the bag and shake to coat.
Spread the potatoes in a single layer on a cookie sheet that has been coated with both Pam and margarine (about 1/2 cube).
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Turn about every 20 minutes.
These are delicious hot, cold or warmed over.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream cheese and sugar, then add fruit to cheese mixture. Stir in Cool Whip.
Must be put in freezer overnight.
Can be taken out 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: In large pot, cook onion, and potatoes in chicken broth until potatoes are medium tender (but not cooked).
Add fish and simmer additional 10 minutes. Stir in the two milks and continue to simmer for approximately 15 to 20 minutes until fish is flaky (not mushy).
Garnish chowder in serving bowl with paprika.
Can serve with biscuits or crackers.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces; spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown meat and onion in a large skillet, breaking up meat with a large spoon as it cooks.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon meat mixture over cabbage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with tinfoil and bake in oven at 350° until cabbage is tender.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Combine eggs, cheese, sugar, salt and extracts; beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream; pour into Graham Nut Crust.
Trim with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° or until just set.
Cool. Chill about 4 to 5 hours.
(Filling will be soft.)
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Makes 10 servings.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit, then mix all ingredients together and chill. (The colored marshmallows look and taste the best.) This is better when made the day before.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip until smooth and spread on cooled crust, then layer peaches and top with the following.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 4 tablespoons flour and 4 tablespoons peach Jell-O.
Stir in water and cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Will need to boil a few minutes.

title: chocolate peanut bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cake mix, 2/3 cup peanut butter and egg until crumbly. Press into a greased 9 x 13 x 3-inch baking pan.

title: barbecue shrimp(for 5 pounds shrimp - with shells)
directions: Mix above in saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place shrimp in broiler pan and pour half the sauce over shrimp.
Cook this under broiler for about 20 minutes.
Turn and pour sauce over this and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve with salad and French bread.
Sauce is great.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix well and add boiling water.
Dip hands in cold water and make out into pones.
Fry in hot oil.
Makes turnip greens flip and peas hop!

title: non-bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Let boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir to mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Let cool and eat!

title: church windows
directions: In Dutch oven melt, low heat, butter and chocolate together stirring occasionally. Take mixture off heat. Stir in marshmallows. Spread half mixture in log shape on wax paper, sprinkle with chopped nuts. Roll up in log shape and place in freezer. Take out of freezer and slice just before serving. Makes 2 logs.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs. Add other ingredients; beat well.
Pour into two greased pie pans (makes its own crust).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: caldo con queso
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine water, green chili peppers, tomato, onion, garlic powder and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cream of potato soup and evaporated milk; heat through.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Makes 4 side dish servings.

title: easy fanned potatoes(microwave)
directions: With a sharp knife, slice potatoes thinly to 1/2-inch from the bottom.
Place on a microwave tray and brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley or chives.
Microwave on Full power for 10 minutes, turning tray after 5 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese, fanning slices gently with a fork, so that cheese falls in between slices.
Microwave 6 minutes longer, until tender and cheese is melted.
Serve as main dish with a salad for light supper.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in large bowl.
Melt cheese and margarine on low heat in saucepan.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and add vanilla.
Then add to sugar and cocoa mixture, mixing well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Cool and cut into pieces.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, mix sugars, margarine, egg, water and vanilla.
Add in the dry ingredients and mix well.
Blend in chips and nuts.

title: catfish italian
directions: Sprinkle fish with paprika.
Place in metal pan sprayed with Pam.
Combine tomato sauce and seasonings.
Pour mixture over fish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle fish with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted.

title: pennsylvania dutch snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix until well blended. Form into small balls.
Roll in the sugar and cinnamon (which have been mixed together).
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Very good.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir together flour, sugar and cornmeal.
Stir together egg whites, oil and milk.
Add baking powder to liquids and dissolve completely.
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
Mix just until smooth.
Pour into greased 7 or 8-inch pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with canned milk, a little at a time, until well blended.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it comes to a boil. Cool slightly and pour into pie shell and cover with cream when completely cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: salem college iced tea
directions: Add mint and cloves to water and bring to a boil. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Add tea and allow to steep for 10 to 15 minutes. Strain, while hot. Add fruit juices and sugar.
This step is important.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Serve chilled, garnished with lemon slices or sprigs of mint.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix water, Jell-O, pineapple and bananas and top with marshmallows; let jell.
Mix and cook remaining ingredients until thick and cool, except Cool Whip.
Mix Cool Whip into cooled mix and spread over salad.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet melt butter; then pour broccoli in and saute until completely thawed.
Remove from heat and stir in Cheez Whiz.
Pour mixture in a large casserole dish and mix in all remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly and light brown.

title: ranch baked beans
directions: Brown beef, onions and peppers until brown.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Add beef mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep fried won tons
directions: Fry and crumble sausage, drain grease.
Let stand.
Mix sausage, chestnuts and green onions.
Put a teaspoon of mixture in the center of the square won ton skin.
Fold the won ton skin to make a triangle.
Seal with water.
Put the filled won ton triangle in very hot oil.
Brown evenly and enjoy.

title: polly's chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix liquid ingredients in bigger bowl.
Dump dry ingredients into bigger bowl and mix with spoon. Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with thin chocolate icing or eat plain.

title: blackberry mush
directions: Combine sugar and 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Stir in blackberries.
Reduce heat, simmer and stir about 5 minutes.
Crush berries.
Blend together cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir into blackberries.
Heat and stir until thick and clear. Stir in lemon juice.
Let cool.

title: pecan  tarts
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese; add flour. Blend and refrigerate for about 1 hour. Shape into small tart pans like crust. Mix egg, brown sugar and salt. Spoon into tart crust. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Can freeze.

title: marian's dessert
directions: Combine Ritz
crackers and melted oleo.
Mix up instant pudding and combine with softened ice cream and milk.

title: mock glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together except jello.
After thoroughly mixing, add jello and mix again.
Refrigerate to let flavors blend.

title: nut bread
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Let stand 20 minutes before putting into a 350° oven and baking for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked breakfast
directions: Grease 9 X 13 pan.
Pat bread and cheese on bottom of pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.	Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cut into squares and serve.

title: ultimate double chocolate brownies
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool.

title: spicy cocktail wieners
directions: Heat over hot water or in microwave the prepared mustard, mixed with the red currant jelly.
Add franks and heat thoroughly. Serve hot from chafing dish, electric frying pan or crock-pot.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
