Measure bran flakes cereal and milk into a large mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.

title: turkey balls
directions: Mix ground turkey, cream cheese and miracle whip and refrigerate for a couple of hours. Form into balls and roll them into the parsley flakes and nuts.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until knife comes out clean and the top is browned.

title: baked apple surprise
directions: Bake apple at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with raisins, honey and cinnamon.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Combine pumpkin, pumpkin spice and fruit pectin.
Heat over high heat until very hot.
Stir in sugar.
Stir until mixture boils over most of the surface.
Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: puppy chow
directions: In large microwavable bowl, melt together the margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir frequently and melt until smooth enough to be stirred to an even consistency.
Add cereal of choice and stir gently until cereal is well coated.
Transfer mixture to a large paper grocery sack (I'm not kidding!).
Add confectioners sugar.
Holding top of bag closed, shake bag well until sugar coats Puppy Chow.
Enjoy!

title: mexican dish
directions: Season meat as desired; brown with onion.
Add soup, milk and Ro-Tel to meat mixture.
In a large, glass Pyrex dish (sprayed with a light coat of cooking oil), spread chips, slightly broken. Next, add meat mixture over chips.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: company broccoli
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Mix with stick of melted margarine.
Put 1/2 of mixture in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Cut the Velveeta cheese into cubes.
Put cooked broccoli on top of cheese. Add the other half of cracker mixture to top of broccoli. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In large saucepan, bring milk and beaten egg yolks to a boil, stirring constantly. Add dry ingredients. Cook until thick; add butter and stir until butter melts. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour into crust.

title: instant chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and sift into container.
Add hot water to each cup (1 1/2 to 2 scoops to taste).

title: scotcharoos
directions: In a saucepan, melt the first 3 ingredients. Continue to stir until it boils. Remove from heat and add the Rice Krispies.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Let sit.
While that is sitting, melt the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together.
Put on top of your other mixture in the 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate or set out, covered.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Separate eggs and beat yolks.
Mix yolks with sugar and butter.
Add whiskey and syrup.
Mix spices and baking powder in 3 cups flour.
Use 1 cup flour on nuts, dates and raisins to coat.
Add these and cherries to cake mixture. Beat whites of eggs to stand up, but not dry.
Fold into mixture. Place few of cherries and pecans on top of cake for decoration.
I put cake in 10-inch tube pan lined with greased brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions for salad use; drain.
Combine macaroni, chicken, cucumber, radishes and cheese.
Toss gently with a mixture of mayonnaise, Italian dressing, salt and pepper.
Chill.
Just before serving, toss 1/2 can French fried onions; garnish with remaining onions.
Serves 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In salad bowl, add macaroni, pepper, tomato, cucumber, carrot and green onions.
Add Mrs. Dash.
Mix well.
Thirty minutes before serving, pour small bottle of Italian dressing over salad and mix.
Best chilled.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Mix together
flour,
oats,
brown sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Put
on
top
of	fruit
mixed with sugar and flour. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butterfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flavoring and work flour and nuts into it. Roll into fingers. Bake in ungreased pan at 325° for 30 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: strawberry margarita pie
directions: In blender or food processor, combine strawberries, cream cheese, lime juice, tequila and orange peel. Blend or process until combined. Pour mixture into medium bowl; fold in whipped topping. Gently pour into pie crust. Freeze until firm, 4 to 6 hours or overnight. Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before serving. Garnish with fresh strawberry slices and mint leaves, if desired. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: turkey sausage supper
directions: Heat the margarine or oil in a skillet; brown the sausages. Add the carrots and 1 cup water; cover and simmer until the carrots are not quite tender.
Add the red pepper and mushrooms and sherry.
Cover and cook a few more minutes until the vegetables are tender but not mushy.
(Meanwhile, cook the rice, the amount you'll need for the number of people you plan to serve.)
Put the rice on a platter or shallow bowl and pour the sausage/vegetable mixture over it.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain well. Add 1/2 stick margarine and cheese; stir until cheese melts. Melt 1/2 stick margarine. Stir in cracker crumbs and pour over cheese and broccoli. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring to boil sugar, syrup and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cornflakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 beaten egg and melted butter.
Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 3 eggs; add powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Beat well and pour over cake mix mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add molasses and egg; mix.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mix.
Chill dough.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 - 10 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well except bread.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Take whole loaf of rye bread; cut out center of bread to make bowl, like a shell.
Tear up bread cut from inside loaf into bite size pieces.
Place shell on a large serving plate.
Fill with dip and arrange cut up pieces around shell and serve.

title: gourmet sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Add next 3 ingredients.
Saute until vegetables are tender. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding, pineapple and juice.
Mix all other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: homemade bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together warm water and yeast.
Let stand until dissolved.
Stir in milk, butter, sugar, salt and enough flour to form a stiff dough.

title: texas cobbler
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Pour margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: chocolate mint snowcaps
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions
using skim milk.
Prepare whipped topping according to package directions substituting peppermint for vanilla and using skim milk. Fold 1/2 cup topping and food coloring together.
Combine remaining whipped topping and pudding.
Divide pudding into 8 dishes and top with 1 tablespoon colored topping. Freeze up to 2 hours and let set at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving. Serves 8.
Contains 120 calories.

title: oatmeal cakes
directions: Mix the oatmeal, egg, sugar and vanilla together.
Mix in enough flour to shape the cakes. Drop on hot greased griddle; brown on both sides.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In glass baking dish, spread cream cheese on bottom, followed by refried beans and then chili. Warm in oven at 350° until warm through. Add cheese and let melt. Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos chips.

title: lillie mae's pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk, blending well. Add vanilla and lemon flavoring and blend.
Turn into well-greased
and floured tube pan or spout pan (approximately 10-inch across top) and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin-nut bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and milk in a large bowl.
Let stand until cereal is softened.
Beat in oil and egg.
Mix in remaining ingredients until just moistened. Spoon in lined muffin pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until center comes out dry on toothpick. Bake for 18 to 23 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Stir in all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Place ribs, meaty side up, on a rack in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until well done, basting with sauce and turning every 30 minutes.

title: chile sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; boil for one hour.
Makes 6 pints.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Grease pan with butter or oil.
In a large bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and butter in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquid is very warm (120° to 130°).
Butter doesn't need to melt.
Gradually add dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer or use hands. Add eggs and 3/4 cup of flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto table.
Cover with hot towel. Let raise 20 minutes or more.
Bake at 350° until done.
Brush butter over rolls.
Serve hot or warm.

title: lemon mustard turkey breasts
directions: Combine all ingredients, except turkey, mixing well.
In large, sealable plastic bag, pour 1 1/4 cups marinade over turkey. Seal and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Chill remaining marinade.
Remove meat from marinade.
Grill or broil meat over indirect heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until meat thermometer inserted in center reaches 170°. Baste frequently with remaining marinade.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Place potatoes in Dutch oven.
Put enough water in to cover potatoes. Cook on medium-high for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add bacon-onion mix, corn and can milk.
Cook until potatoes are done on medium, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: favorite chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of milk in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth. Set aside.

title: sausage roll
directions: Chill. Serve with Fritos corn chips.

title: braised chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium size saucepan.
Cover; heat to boiling and simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover, simmer 15 minutes longer, basting frequently.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook sausage in a large frypan until no longer pink; drain. Add hash browns to sausage and cook until lightly browned. Add beaten eggs and cook until eggs are done and well combined with sausage and potatoes.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.

title: rose hill berries
directions: Sprinkle a little sugar over strawberries.
Mix sour cream and maple syrup.
Divide strawberries among 6 to 8 dishes.
Sprinkle brown sugar over each and top with sour cream mixture.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Mix cornstarch with a little water to make smooth paste.
Add to first mixture, then add milk and salt.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from stove and add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Add beaten whites of eggs or reserve for a meringue.
Pour into a baked crust.
If meringue is used, spread on top and return to oven to brown.
Whipped topping may be used instead of meringue.

title: chinese new year rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli stuffing
directions: Mix stuffing mix according to instructions.
Layer broccoli, cheese and soup in a greased casserole.
Top with prepared stuffing mix.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: oh-so-easy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk and blend into mixture.
Fold whipped topping into mixture.
Pour mixture into pie crusts and freeze until pies are smooth.
Take out of freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 pies.
This can be made several days before serving.

title: double corn bread pudding
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, until brown on top.
Great for potluck supper!

title: deluxe chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken; boil until tender.
Save broth.
Cool chicken and cut up.
Saute peppers and onions in butter.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth; do not drain.
While hot, add cheese in chunks and stir until melted.
Then add Ro-Tel, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms and peas.
Add peppers and onions and cut-up chicken. Season with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Put slivered toasted almonds on top.
Cook at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: orange bread
directions: Cream butter; slowly add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add orange rind and well-beaten egg.
Add orange juice and milk alternately with flour, baking powder and salt which have been sifted together.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Butter and flour Bundt cake pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
Drip and brush glaze until all glaze is used.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Beat everything together until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake about 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pots de creme woodward
directions: Scald milk.
Add to a blender which has been warmed by adding hot water and then dried.
Pour all ingredients, except whipped cream and shaved chocolate.
Blend at high speed and fill pots or stemmed wine glasses, leaving room for cream.
Refrigerate 3 to 8 hours.
Top with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the crumbs, 2 tablespoons of sugar and butter; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: not for wimps texas chili
directions: Brown meat in pan with onion, bell pepper, chili powder, garlic powder, pepper and salt.
Add tomato and chili mix and 1 cup water.
Add extra character with 1/2 cup beer (any kind). Bring to boil, then simmer over low fire or in slow cooker.
Come back in 2 hours; enjoy.
Delicious over steamed rice.

title: icebox pie
directions: Line bottom of pan with wafer crumbs.
Mix sugar, egg, vanilla and butter.
Place over crumbs.
Whip cream, fold in cherries, nuts and pineapple.
Place on top and sprinkle with more crumbs. Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, covered; last 10 minutes uncovered.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Eat with corn chips.

title: one pan pork chops and fixins
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place pork chops.
Season well. Peel potatoes and slice into 1/4-inch slabs.
Place on chops. Season potatoes.
Slice onions thin and add.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut crunch salad
directions: Toss cabbage and celery together.
Chill.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, salt, onion, green pepper and cucumber in small bowl. Chill.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Add next 6 ingredients to drippings; cover and cook for 10 minutes over medium heat, turning cabbage once.
Add sausage; cover and cook 7 minutes.
Transfer to serving dish with slotted spoon; sprinkle with bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell and cover with lattice crust.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 45 minutes.
(Start at 400°, and turn down if it gets brown.)

title: chocolate-almond pralines
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and almonds in heavy pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook mixture to soft ball stage (238°), stirring constantly.
Remove mixture from heat and stir in chocolate and Kahlua, if desired.
Beat with a wooden spoon just until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop mixture by tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased waxed paper and let pralines stand until firm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots in diagonal slices.
Cook with 1 teaspoon salt for 10 minutes; cool.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, onion, 3/4 teaspoon salt, paprika and dry mustard; blend in blender.
To dressing, add olives, onions, relish, parsley and capers.
Mix and pour over carrots.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Pour batter into 2 pie pans.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and brush well with dressing. Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and broil for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: nisua (finnish coffee bread)
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar.
Stir.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour into large bowl.
Add yeast, cardamom seed, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat in 2 eggs, margarine and shortening.
Stir in 4 to 5 cups flour, mixing well.
Add up to 1 cup flour while kneading dough until it leaves sides of bowl and hands.
Let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled in size.
Punch down; let rise 1/2 hour longer. Shape into loaves or braids in greased pans.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
When cool, frost, if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: First add eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Add flour and zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves of bread.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat milk and lemon juice together with a mixer.
Fold in pineapple and nuts and mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix well. Pour into 8-inch pie shells.*
Refrigerate before serving. Freezes very well.
Makes 2 pies.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
shortening;
add
sugars
and cream again. Add
eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.	Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil cranberries in pint of water until soft.
Strain through sieve.
Set aside.
Combine in a pan the sugar, 1 quart of water and red hots.
Boil until dissolved.
Squeeze the juice from oranges and lemon.
Mix all ingredients together with 2 quarts of water.
Serve hot.

title: crab dip
directions: Mash cream cheese well.
Work in other ingredients.
Heat in double boiler or crock-pot.
Add crabmeat about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine chili sauce and jelly over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Drop in franks and cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: huevos rancheros
directions: Heat oil and soften tortillas on both sides by dipping them in hot oil.
Drain and set aside in warmer.
Fry eggs, sunny side up, then place eggs over tortillas.
Top with salsa and cheese. Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (I use Pam).
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: spotson
directions: Beat all together with a knife (should be thick dough).
Cut into boiling turkey or chicken broth.
Let simmer a few minutes until spotson is done.

title: dough bubbles
directions: Thaw bread dough and let rise once.
Cut dough into 32 pieces. Wrap each piece of dough around a piece of cheese and meat, forming balls.
Dip balls in melted butter and garlic powder. Layer in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and let rise until the dough fills the dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very frothy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until solid peaks form and sugar is dissolved.
Fold in pecans and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Top with quartered cherries.
Place in preheated oven.
After 30 seconds, turn off oven and leave until morning or at least 5 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, marshmallows or coconut, pineapple, cherries and nuts in bowl. Chill milk in the refrigerator tray until soft crystals form around edges of tray (15 to 20 minutes). Whip until stiff, 1 minute. Add lemon juice and whip very stiff (2 minutes). Beat in sugar. Fold whipped milk into rice mixture. Spoon into serving dishes.

title: wilted leaf lettuce
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Reserve drippings.
Add onions to drippings and cook until tender.
Add vinegar, 1/4 cup water, sugar and bacon to the onions.
Stir until it boils.
Pour hot dressing over lettuce.
Toss to coat.
Garnish with chopped egg. Serves 6.

title: lisa's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together egg, oil and vanilla.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add flour.
Stir until desired stiffness (you may increase or decrease amount of flour slightly), then stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet by heaping tablespoon 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in preheated 375° oven.

title: bayou belle jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in butter.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: lime jello mold
directions: You will need a 1 1/2-quart Jell-O mold.

title: aunt mary's meat and macaroni
directions: Saute onion and garlic; add meat and brown.
When brown, add cinnamon, salt, pepper, mint and tomato sauce and one can water. While meat is getting brown, cook spaghetti almost done.
Brown butter for spaghetti; place layer of meat, then spaghetti, etc. Cover with milk and egg mixture; shake and sprinkle with cheese. Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: potato drop donuts
directions: Mix everything together and drop from a spoon into 375° cooking oil.
Cook until brown, then shake in bag of sugar.

title: iowa corn fritters
directions: Heat 3-inches of oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Stir together baking mix, water and egg until smooth.
Stir in corn. Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown on both sides. Drain and serve hot with syrup.

title: oriental rice
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add rice and brown lightly.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover the baking dish with foil and a lid.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Do not uncover during baking process.
Let sit, still covered, for 30 minutes before serving.
Follow directions exactly and do not substitute.

title: cheese dip
directions: Dump all this in a slow cooker and melt.
Serve warm.

title: veal supreme
directions: Cut celery fine.
Brown in shortening.
Add veal and brown well.
Sift 1/4 cup flour over top of meat and season with salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms, soup and water and simmer 45 minutes. Add more water if too thick.
Put hot mixture in buttered casserole.
Cover with noodles and almonds.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° or until noodles are crisp and almonds slightly browned.

title: sausage cheese bread
directions: Let bread dough thaw and rise overnight with melted butter on top. Roll out on floured surface into a rectangular shape. Brown sausage with onion and drain off grease. Layer sausage and cheeses on bread. Roll into a log with seams down and pinch ends under. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together oil, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas.
Combine in a medium casserole dish. Add mushroom soup and cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 300° until bubbly, about 15 to 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange chicken in single layer.
In sieve, rinse sauerkraut in cold water, then press out liquid.
Sprinkle kraut evenly on chicken.
Cover kraut with cheese slices.
Pour dressing on top.
Cover pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecan pieces over unbaked crust.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Bring first five ingredients to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add cranberry sauce and chopped apple.
Pour into mold and place in refrigerator to set.

title: grilled marinated flank steak
directions: Combine wine, sherry, garlic and seasonings together.
Make very thin slashes diagonally across the grain of the steak.
Put steak in a long glass baking dish and pour marinade over the steak.
Cover and chill for 12 to 18 hours.
Turn steak over once during this time.
Preheat grill (gas) or prepare charcoal.
Grill meat 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 8 (3 ounce) servings.

title: favorite chili
directions: Simmer dry beans in three times their volume of unsalted water for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand, covered, for an hour and a half or until softened.
Drain well.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker in order listed.
Stir once.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high for 5 to 6 hours).

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix ranch dressing, sour cream, sugar, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Stir well to combine.
In a large salad bowl place onion, cauliflower, and lettuce.
Add dressing mixture and toss to coat vegetables.
Top with bacon bits.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Fry meat, onion and seasonings.
Add drained beans and soup. Put mashed potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and make a well.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Place in 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cowgirl cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside the flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend eggs, shortening and sugars.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add oats, vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Dough will be crumbly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: friendship sourdough bread
directions: Using a wooden spoon, mix these ingredients in a large bowl. You should have a stiff batter. (You may have to use your hands to mix completely.)
Grease another bowl. Add dough and turn it over so it is greased on all sides.
Cover lightly with wax paper or plastic wrap.
Do not refrigerate.
Let stand overnight.

title: cauliflower and pea salad
directions: Break up the cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Add the peas and celery (dice celery into small pieces).
Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over the vegetables.
Stir to coat well.

title: spiced friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Use 1 1/2 teaspoons tea mix per 1 cup hot water.
Makes a pretty present.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Grate cheese. Add jar of pimentos (with juice). Season with lemon pepper. Mix in mayonnaise until reaches consistency you like.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix chicken, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Then mix dressing, broth and margarine or butter.
Pour half of dressing mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 11-inch loaf pan.
Place chicken next.
Then pour soup mixture over.
Put remainder of dressing mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water; let soften 10 minutes.
Add remaining water and sugar, salt, shortening and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth (I use an electric mixer with dough hooks).
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top of dough.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
(I place in cold oven with a pan of hot water and it rises faster.)
Divide in half, roll out
and put in pans.
(I just put it in the pans and then roll and push to make it fit.)

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix jello per box instructions.
When mixture begins to set, add strawberries and Cool Whip.
Stir well and refrigerate covered.

title: irene's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugars.
Add 1 well beaten egg and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or more.

title: salad
directions: Whip the Cool Whip.
Add milk.
Whip again.
Mix pineapple and pineapple pie filling and whip again.
Mix in some chopped pecans, as desired.
Chill.

title: dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bacon potato soup
directions: Slice the leeks lengthwise. Remove the root end and most of the green end. Slice the leeks across the grain and soak in water until needed. Add the bacon pieces to a heavy sauce pan and cook until brown. Add the celery and leeks. Cook until just soft. Add the flour and cook for 3 minutes. Add the water and milk. Slowly bring to a boil. Reduce the heat, add the potatoes and simmer for 1 hour, or until the vegetables are tender. Check the seasonings. Serve warm, garnish with parsley. Serves 4.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix together cream cheese, egg and 1/3 cup sugar until creamy. Add chocolate tidbits and set aside.
Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in dry ingredients; add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix with spoon (batter is thin).

title: busy day casserole
directions: Spread ground beef in a casserole.
Cover with onions and bacon.
Cover with cooked rice.
Add tomatoes.
Season to taste. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box; set aside.
Mix milk, shredded chicken and soups together in 2-quart casserole dish and top with stuffing.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes in a 425° oven, then uncover and brown.

title: james' favorite cookies
directions: In a large bowl, use an electric mixer to cream shortening and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour until there are no traces of white seen.
Work in oats, pecans and coconut.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls, 3 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until edges begin to turn brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Centers will be soft.
Remove from pan to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: my parent's skillet kraut
directions: Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Pour off most of grease.
Add the sauerkraut (drained partially) to the bacon and fryings.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, to avoid scorching.
Add sugar gradually as it is cooking, tasting until you achieve the sweet and sour taste you prefer.

title: chocolate ice cream dessert
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine and chocolate.
Add beaten egg yolks and sugar.
Add chopped nuts, pinch of salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla. When cool, beat the 3 egg whites and fold in.
Pour this over crushed vanilla wafers and melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool in refrigerator.

title: baked hamburger stuffed zucchini
directions: Pre-boil zucchini - 3 minutes for small or longer for large. Cut in half length-wise. Remove pulp (set aside) and sprinkle shell with salt and pepper. Melt butter in fry pan. Add celery, onions and meat to butter and cook until brown. Add bread cubes, pulp of zucchini and tomato sauce. Stuff into zucchini shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in shallow pan in 375 degree oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Cream oleo and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and mix until smooth.
Add coconut and nuts.
Form into egg shape and let stand overnight.
Melt chocolate and wax in saucepan.
Dip eggs in mixture and place on waxed paper to set.

title: pat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, and beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add oats, cereal and coconut.
Drop on greased cookie sheets and pat down with glass that is coated with powdered sugar.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 10 minutes.

title: raised dough with cream cheese filling
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large mixing bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Add sour cream mixture, eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll each into an 8 x 12-inch sheet.
Fill with filling.

title: cauliflower pickles
directions: Wash cauliflower and divide into florets.
Combine onions, red pepper and salt; cover with ice cubes.
Let set 3 to 4 hours. Drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Add cauliflower and onions.
Boil 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove red pepper and pack vegetables into hot jars. Cut red pepper into pieces and put in each jar.
Yield: 5 pints.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar in bowl.
Mix well.
Combine pudding mix and milk in mixer bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add whipped topping; beat well.
Add pudding mixture to cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Reserve enough cookie crumbs for topping.
Alternate layers of cookie crumbs and pudding mixture in large flowerpot until all ingredients are used. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Garnish with miniature silk flowers, gummy worms and toy garden tools.

title: pot roast
directions: In a pan, brown the roast in shortening on both sides, then put in a pot.
Add 2 cups water to the onion soup and pour over the roast with the mushroom soup.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until almost tender, then add carrots and potatoes and cook until done.

title: easy moussaka
directions: Place eggplant slices on cookie sheet and brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and broil for 5 minutes or until golden.
Turn slices and brush and season again and brown second side.

title: muddy halloween worms
directions: Mix up batch of chocolate pudding with jelly worms and put cookie crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle with Fritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until slightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
This is especially good on grilled chicken.
Spread over chicken after turning on the grill.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice (uncooked) in casserole dish. Put chicken on rice. Mix soup and water and pour over chicken and rice. Sprinkle onion soup mix. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° about an hour or until chicken is tender. Check occasionally to see if a little more liquid is needed.

title: ukrainian nut roll
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk; add margarine, sugar and salt.
When lukewarm, add enough flour to make a thick batter.
Add to yeast and eggs.
Beat well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until satiny.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix and put into baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds on top. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw frozen spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir in soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts, pimentos and green onion.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Cut middle from Hawaiian bread and put dip in middle.
Cut middle of bread in bite size pieces and serve with dip.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 40 to 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy meat and potato meal
directions: In a skillet or Corningware pan, place diced potatoes. Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Cover with 1 cup
of milk.
Lay pork chops on top and bake in 350° oven for about 1 or 1 1/2 hours. Turn pork chops once.

title: irish cream dream cake
directions: Place first five ingredients in mixing bowl and blend with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Grease and dust Bundt cake pan with flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 50 minutes and remove from pan.

title: fantastic stuffing
directions: Moisten the 2 bags of bread cubes.
Add all ingredients.
Add mushroom soup directly from can.
Mix well and stuff.

title: iced spiced coffee
directions: Pick a handful of green needles.
Simmer in a pot of water until desired strength is reached.
This is delicious when camping out and you are waiting for your dinner to cook.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water, butter, vinegar and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing brownies
directions: Mix dressing, water, vanilla and nuts with dry ingredients. Bake in a flat long pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice.

title: diane's deviled chicken spread
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Chill, if desired before serving.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Add small bits of pimiento cheese to soft Cheddar cheese.
Mix well.
Keep adding more pimiento bits until mixture is pleasing to the taste.
Spread on rye or any other choice of bread.
Add crisp bacon, if desired.
Grill in lightly greased frypan or sandwich grill.

title: pizza turnovers
directions: Combine cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Halve each biscuit horizontally, making 20.
Gently shape each piece of dough into an oval about 2 1/2 x 4-inches and place a slice of pepperoni in center top with a tablespoon of cheese mixture. Moisten edges and seal pocket.
Cook for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian style popcorn
directions: In a pan, cook and stir margarine, Italian seasoning and garlic powder until margarine melts.
Toss with cheese.
Makes 10 cups (20 servings).

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, stirring well. Pour into greased casserole dish. Mix butter and corn flakes. Press onto top of potato mixture. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add dry ingredients together.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Rinse.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients except Mozzarella.
Layer half the noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread with the Ricotta filling.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese, then half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: good-n-easy candy
directions: Melt chocolate in pan with shortening.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Add M&M's last.
Spread on buttered cookie pan.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: noodles and cheese
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Drain.
Mix in margarine until melted.
Add sour cream and cottage cheese.
Mix together well. Great hot or cold.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead until smooth, dry and pliable. Cover and let rise until double in size.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Brush entire surface with egg wash.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar, raisins and nuts.
Roll dough up like a jelly roll and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in pan and let rise.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons in mug of boiling water.
Store mixture in airtight container for storage.

title: clam dip(cream cheese recipe)
directions: Drain clams, reserving 1 tablespoon clam juice.
Soften the cream cheese with the clam juice.
Add remaining ingredients and beat into cream cheese mixture. Mix in clams.
Chill and serve on crackers or with chips or vegetable dippers.

title: harvest bread
directions: Slice bread into 1-inch thick slices. Place in a pan. Drizzle slices heavy with olive oil. Place onions and tomatoes on top of bread. Add Feta and Parmesan cheese liberally on top with black pepper. Put under broiler until golden brown. Slice olives on top. Serve hot.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Place chopped peppers, onion and pineapple on paper towel to absorb liquid.
Blend ingredients well.
Chill at least 1/2 hour. Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Note:
May substitute 1 stick margarine and 1/2 stick butter for shortening.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
Melt butter in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Stir in brown sugar until blended. Remove from heat.
Arrange pineapple slices in sugar mixture. Place cherry in center of each slice.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and shortening; beat 2 minutes.
Add egg, reserved syrup and vanilla, beat 2 minutes.
Pour over pineapple in skillet, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack, 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate. Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cornbread meal in one
directions: Brown meat and onion; add sauce and corn.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Pour half of cornbread mixture into a deep skillet.
Add beef mixture.
Top with grated cheese, then pour remaining cornbread mix on top.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: essie's cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Stir sifted dry ingredients in alternately with milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon fruit over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Pour fruit juice over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
During baking, the fruit and juice go to the bottom and a cake-like layer forms on top.
Serve warm.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Break biscuits in half and shake in sugar mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans in while placing biscuits.
In saucepan, mix brown sugar, 3/4 cup sugar and butter until hot.
Do not boil!
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: lime pie
directions: Let mixture come to a boil.
Mix all ingredients.
Place the mixture into an 8 or 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Place in freezer for 10 or 15 minutes for quick setting.
Ready to serve in approximately 20 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Add salt and soda to flour and sift 5 times.
After sifting, measure again.
Cream butter and margarine; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, one tablespoon at a time, along with whipping cream.
Add flavoring.
Mix well. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325° or until straw comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° until pie is firm, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: executive meeting chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Season to taste with salt and pepper or Greek seasoning.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serves at least 12, depending on size of servings.
Excellent!

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
Add shortening, vanilla, milk, and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake in a well greased 9-inch tube pan.
Temperature 375° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: honey baked onions
directions: Place onions in 9-inch square pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over onions.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Use an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Layer in order given. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with corn chips.

title: baked chicken in browning bag
directions: Line large flat pan with aluminum foil.
Place large size browning bag in bottom of pan.
Mix flour and cornstarch together and put in bottom of bag.
Put salt, pepper and lots of paprika all over chicken pieces.
Place side by side in browning bag. Pour wine and water mixed together over chicken.
Put onion in bag.
Twist and close bag with twister.
Prick 5 holes in bag. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Place walnuts on baking sheet at 275° for 10 minutes.
Bring next four ingredients to boil and boil for 2 minutes, stirring.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Stir and add nuts.
Stir to coat.
Remove to wax paper or foil with slotted spoon.
Separate with fork and let dry 20 to 30 minutes.
Store in jars.

title: candied pecans
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart microwave casserole for 30 to 45 seconds.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts until well coated.
Microwave 3 minutes. Spread nuts on waxed paper to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain thoroughly.
Mix in all remaining ingredients except crumbs and butter.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and beginning to brown for about 30 minutes.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, milk, bread crumbs, catsup, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into loaf with wet hands and place in center of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer around meat loaf, carrots, potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle each layer with parsley flakes, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Place strawberries in 2-quart glass bowl or casserole.
Place in microwave; set timer for 10 minutes.
After 2 minutes, stir Sure-Jell into thawed strawberries.
Cook approximately 2 minutes or until a few bubbles show on top.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring every 2 minutes.
Pour into glass jars and refrigerate.
Yields 3 cups.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Shred cheese and place in double boiler along with half of the milk.
Continue to add the milk a little at a time, stirring frequently.
Cheese should be thick like pudding.
Remove from heat and add pimento.
Pour into jars and store in refrigerator.

title: canaduls(salami soup)
directions: Make up beef broth with beef roast.
Cut into cubes, carrots, celery, onions and tomatoes.
Fry onions, celery, bacon and salami together.
In a bowl mix bread (cubed), eggs and flour enough to make bread mixture stiff.
Mix all fried ingredients with bread mixture.
Make into medium-sized balls.
Drop into broth and cook.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add butter and 2 cups cheese; stir. Add milk, beaten eggs, can of milk and salt and pepper to taste. Pour in crock-pot and stir.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover; cook for 3 hours on low.
Do not stir until done.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in 2-inch balls.
Put on cookie sheet to bake.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sauce for yams
directions: Bring sauce to a boil; add drained yams and cook at low heat about 5 minutes.
This can be done ahead and then reheated.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries, sweetener and water in 3 quart pan.
Heat the mixture and add some of the liquid to the cornstarch.
Add cornstarch back to the strawberry mixture.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour into pie shell and chill thoroughly.
Prior to serving whip the cream and place on top of pie.
Serve and enjoy!

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle equal amounts on top of cream cheese.
Or mix all ingredients and spread on top of tortillas.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours. Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces; discard ends.
Serve with spirals facing up.

title: pasta and mushroom sauce
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Stir in milk and bring to a bubble.
Add seasoning and cook about 2 minutes or until thickened.
Mix with pasta and serve immediately.

title: beef casserole stew
directions: Layer half of the meat, sprinkled with 1/4 cup flour.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Sprinkle remaining flour; repeat layers.
Mix water, sherry, soy sauce, salt and pepper. Pour over all.
Cover and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Add green peppers and cook 20 minutes longer.
Delicious!!

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in big bowl in microwave.
Add 2 cups to 4 cups Rice Krispies according to liking.
Mix well using plastic spoon coated with butter.
Butter pans to chill treats in.
Empty mixture into pans.
Spread evenly and put into refrigerator about 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Then cut into squares and then eat.

title: kajun kabobs
directions: Take about half-dozen bamboo skewers and begin alternating the kabob ingredients on the stick as follows:
onion, chicken breast, celery, smoked sausage, mushroom, pork loin, zucchini and round steak.
Fill the skewer, but leave a 2-inch open space in the center, then cut it to make 2 small kabobs.
Salt and pepper the kabobs and set aside.
Season the flour with salt and pepper to make a dusting mix and whip the eggs into the milk to make the egg wash.
Roll a kabob in the flour, then dip it in the egg wash and roll it back in the flour again.
Allow the coated kabob to "rest" on the counter about 3 to 5 minutes so that the coating sticks well.
Heat the oil to 375° in a chicken fryer or Dutch oven. Lower the kabobs into the hot oil one at a time and fry until the coating turns crunchy and crisp.
Drain on absorbent paper towels and serve alongside a piping hot dish of Cajun dirty rice.

title: heaven in a bowl
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and bake in an oblong pan.
Cool and halve.

title: grilled salmon
directions: Baste salmon steaks on both sides with lemon juice.
Sprinkle lemon pepper as desired for flavor.
Place steaks on hot grill and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn steaks and baste again with lemon juice.
Cook for another 3 to 4 minutes.
Fish should flake easily when done.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on a large plate.
Drain crabmeat.
Spread with a fork on top of the cream cheese.
Spread cocktail sauce on top of the crabmeat.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine and mix well first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs, slightly beaten.
Pour into unbaked prepared pie shell.
Sprinkle with shelled pecans halves.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes. Do not let it get too brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll pastry in pan or large cookie sheet.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in brown sugar, mustard and salt. Add cooked carrots.
Heat, stirring constantly until carrots are glazed, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: scandinavian nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
While cake is still warm, remove from pan and frost.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel apples and cut into thin slices.
Mix 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Set aside.
Blend all other ingredients, except baking powder and baking soda, with mixer on low speed for 1 minute and on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add baking soda and baking powder.
Mix 1 minute more.

title: nut crunch
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until stiff.
Add sugar and beat again.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Break into dessert cups and top with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: strawberry show boat
directions: Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Add strawberries and strawberry glaze.
Set aside.
Blend cream cheese with condensed milk.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Layer top layer, then layer with the bottom until all is used up.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: hannah's pasta with garlic, parsley and broccoli
directions: Put a large pot of water on stove to boil.
In a separate pot, steam broccoli florets for about 2 minutes.
Peel and chop the garlic and chop the parsley.
When the water is boiling, add some salt and put in pasta.
When it is nearly cooked, heat olive oil in large saute pan and very gently cook the garlic so it just sizzles. Be careful not to let it brown.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown chops in oil. Remove chops from skillet; pour off fat.
In skillet, combine lemon juice and cornstarch; mix well.
Add sugar, onion, soy sauce, bouillon and reserved syrup; cook and stir until thickened and bouillon is dissolved.
Add pork chops and carrots; cover and bake for 1 hour, or until tender.
Add pineapple and bake 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with green pepper.
Serve with rice, if desired.

title: triple-cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and celery in 10-inch skillet, stirring frequently until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in cottage cheese, hot water, macaroni sauce mix, tomato sauce and cream cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Simmer uncovered until desired consistency.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, sour cream, mushroom soup and cheese together. Spread in glass Pyrex dish.
Crush crackers firmly and spread evenly on top.
Cut butter into squares and place over top of crackers.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread supreme
directions: Sift first 8 ingredients together.
Combine shortening, maple syrup, sour milk and egg.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, beat well and pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and additional cinnamon over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares, top with whipped cream.
Makes 1 (8 x 8-inch) cake.

title: dijon chicken salad sandwich
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Fill croissants with lettuce, tomato and chicken salad.
Serves 6.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and set aside.
Melt cream cheese and Rotel in microwave until cream cheese is thoroughly melted.
Add sausage. Serve with Tostitos or other chips.

title: fried apple pie
directions: Reconstitute apples according to package directions.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add cold water.
Roll into 5-inch circles. Put 1 tablespoon of apple mixture in center of circle.
Fold ends together and crimp around edges.
Cover bottom of frying pan with oil and fry pies on low heat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.

title: no-knead whole wheat bread(from county cork, ireland)
directions: Place the whole wheat flour in large bowl; set it in a very low oven for 21 minutes.
This is to warm the flour and bowl.
If it is a gas oven, the pilot light will give sufficient heat.
If not, improvise.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine flours, baking powder and salt. Cut in oleo until particles are fine.
Add milk and stir until dough clings together.
Knead on lightly floured surface 12 times. Pat out to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles. Place biscuits 1/2 inch apart on baking sheet.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Crush Butterfinger bars into tiny pieces.
Set aside.
Break angel cakes into bite size pieces; set aside.
Mix butter, yolks and sugar until creamy. Whip cream until it "peaks."
Mix butter mixture and whip cream mixture together with a spoon.
Place 1/2 cake in a baking dish.
Place 1/2 cream mixture over cake.
Place 1/2 crushed Butterfinger bars over cream mixture.
Repeat layers.

title: golden punch
directions: Put in large container and freeze.
Thaw 30 minutes.
Place in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and mix well.

title: tennessee hash(microwave)
directions: Brown ground beef in microwave-safe dish.
Drain.
Add soup, corn and cream cheese, cut in cubes.
Stir in.
Microwave on High for 25 minutes or until cream cheese is bubbly.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix together the dry Jell-O, cake mix, oil and water.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat according to directions on cake mix. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste and 6-ounce can of water, season to taste.
Simmer.

title: party pizzas
directions: Split muffins in half using a fork.
Broil to a light brown. Combine the spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and crushed garlic.
Stir thoroughly.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Place 2 tablespoons of sauce on each muffin.
Sprinkle on cheese and sausage, if desired.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and water.
Cook on low until rhubarb mixes well.
Add strawberries (already thawed); cover and cook on low. Good by itself or as an ice cream topping.

title: grannie great's soft sour cream cookie
directions: Combine eggs, shortening, brown sugar, vanilla and sour cream and whip up into airy batter.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold into wet mixture, making a soft dough.
Roll the dough into balls, then flatten with bottom of floured glass.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
This is a cake-like cookie; do not over or under bake.

title: layered noodle bake
directions: Spread thin layer of sauce onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange half of the noodles over sauce.
Cover with half of remaining sauce.
Cover with meat, Ricotta and half of the Mozzarella.
Top with layers of remaining noodles, sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: wheatheart bread
directions: Blend together as listed.
Add enough flour to make a satiny dough.
Turn out on board and work until easy to handle.
Knead 10 minutes and place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch down.
Shape in two parts.
Put in 2 loaf pans.
Let rise to almost double in size.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Stir into shortening mixture.
Chill.

title: delicious tomato pie
directions: Fill crust alternately with layers of tomatoes and onions. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine mayonnaise and sharp cheese.
Spread over tomatoes.
Sprinkle top with crumbled bacon and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banamaranath muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick vegetable spray.
Combine the flours, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in a bowl.
Beat together the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the egg.
Mix in dry ingredients alternately with the mashed bananas and apple juice.
Stir in the nuts.
Spoon the batter into the muffin cups, filling 2/3 full. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to a wire rack for cooling.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: You will also need wax paper.

title: christmas lime salad
directions: Combine the gelatin, marshmallows and sugar with one cup boiling water.
Stir until marshmallows dissolve.
Refrigerate until partially congealed.
Blend in whipped cream, pineapple, cream cheese and pecans.
Chill until set.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: In a bowl combine the uncooked beef, beans, chili powder and oregano. Spoon into uncooked manicotti shells. Arrange in a greased 13 X 9 pan. Combine water, picante sauce and pour over shells. cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for one hour. Uncover and spoon sour cream over top. Sprinkle with cheese and green onions. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer uncovered until cheese melts.

title: ripe cucumber relish
directions: Boil until thick.
Add drained cucumbers and onions.
Bring to a boil.
(This mustard sauce is good for pickled beans.)

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Cream sugar and cheese together.
Add vanilla.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on the package.
Mix Dream Whip and cheese mixture together.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Put a layer of cracker crumbs and butter.
Put a layer of cracker crumbs, layer of Dream Whip mixture and layer of cherries. Repeat.
Chill before serving.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt
butter and let cool. Mix all the ingredients together. Pour in cake pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Put meat and chopped celery and onions in large pan; cook until vegetables are tender.
Add the next 3 ingredients; simmer for a few minutes.
Season generously with chili powder; add 1/2 brick of chili.
Cook slowly, stirring often, until done.
Crush crackers fine; thicken with this.
Eat on buns with sliced cheese.

title: kongo bars
directions: Set oven to 350° and grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine melted butter and brown sugar and beat them until they are thoroughly mixed.
Add the eggs (a little at a time).
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add them to the batter, mixing until the dry ingredients are blended thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Spread batter in greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes for moist bars, 25 minutes for drier version.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini, using peeling.
Beat together eggs, oil, zucchini, vanilla and sugar.
Beat thoroughly.
Mix together in another bowl the flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and soda. Add dry ingredients to zucchini mixture.
(Optional:
Add nuts, raisins or dates.) Makes 2 large loaves or 3 small loaves.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Take out of pans immediately.
Cool on racks.

title: old fashion hermits(cookies)
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients well.
Separately, cream shortening, sugars and eggs together well.
Blend in flour mixture.
Add raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies. Delicious!

title: microwave fresh corn cheese quiche
directions: Microwave bacon slices on covered paper plate or dish on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp. Set aside.
Cut corn off cob and set aside. Combine eggs, milk, cheese, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Microwave on Medium 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through. Stir well and add corn.
Pour mixture into the baked pie shell.
Microwave on Medium 13 to 17 minutes or until firm around edges.
Center should be slightly soft, but will firm on standing. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Arrange bacon slices over top and garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: aunt helen's potato latkes
directions: Beat mixture together.
Heat oil (hot!) in frypan and drop by tablespoon.
Fry until brown.
Flip over and fry.
Eat! Eat! Enjoy!

title: rocky roads(candy)
directions: Melt chocolate pieces over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows and nutmeats.
Add cherries and citron.
Spread in wax paper lined dish and chill until set.
Cut into small squares.

title: mornay chicken with pasta
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper to make a smooth paste.
Add warm milk slowly to butter mixture.
Simmer and stir 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir egg yolks and 6 tablespoons Parmesan cheese quickly into white sauce.
Stir chicken and broccoli into sauce.
Toss sauce with spaghetti.
Place in a large jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Place under broiler and brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Add whole chicken. Top with salt, pepper and liquid.
Sprinkle basil over top.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, on high for 3 1/2 to 5 hours, using 1 cup water.

title: easy chicken dish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish. Skin chicken pieces and lay on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over roast.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill until ready to serve.
Use any type of fruit.

title: pecan caramels
directions: In large heavy saucepan, boil sugar and corn syrup to firm ball stage (245°), stirring occasionally.
Add butter and half and half, stirring so slowly that syrup does not stop boiling at any time.
Again cook rapidly, stirring constantly, to 245°.
Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla and nuts.
Pour into well-buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into bite-sized pieces and wrap each in waxed paper.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: Combine bananas, lemon juice and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 1 1/2 hours or overnight.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: lee's luscious milk chocolate
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch or jelly roll pan with margarine; put in refrigerator.
Dump sugar, milk and butter into heavy-duty pot. Put chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme into large bowl.
Bring mixture in pot to boil.
Start timer and stir vigorously for 10 minutes.
Pour over goop in bowl.
Add vanilla and nuts and mix real good.
Pour into greased pan.
Do not refrigerate.

title: easy delicious punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemonade that you have mixed.
Add pineapple and apricot juices.
Stir thoroughly.
Chill thoroughly.
Make ice ring out of part of mixture.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes approximately 20 cups.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Combine with all of the remaining ingredients except cheese and pepperoni.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan.
Top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: deanie's sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven, then put topping on.

title: carrots with mint
directions: Clean the carrots.
If 2 inches long, leave whole.
Otherwise, cut 1/4-inch thick.
Cook in lightly salted boiling water until tender.
Drain, return carrots to the pan; add butter and sugar. Stir over very low heat for 3 to 4 minutes until fairly dried out. Add the mint and mix well.

title: zucchini square
directions: Peel zucchini; cut in 4ths and cube.
Stir everything together in large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 10-inch glass dish until golden color.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Combine chocolate mint wafer crumbs with melted butter and press into 9-inch pie pan to make crust.
Chill at least 20 minutes.

title: my quiche
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer 6 slices of bread and then 2 cups of cheese twice.
Mix milk, eggs and mustard and pour over layers.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Place casserole in a pan of hot water and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: twin roast chicken
directions: Sprinkle neck and body cavities of two whole frying chickens with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon Accent.
Heat 2 tablespoons corn oil in 10-inch frypan.
Add onions, garlic and green pepper. Sprinkle with remaining 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon Accent. Cook over moderate heat, stirring, for 5 minutes.

title: orange swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of the batter and set aside.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Stir gelatin (dry) and extract into the 1 1/2 c. batter.
Drop orange batter by generous tbsp. randomly in 6 to 8 mounds onto batter in pan.
Cut through batter with knife in S-shaped curves in one continuous motion for swirled effect.
Bake 42 to 47 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Turn upside down onto heatproof serving plate; remove pan. Cool cake completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beef egg rolls
directions: Brown hamburger and partially drain.
Add next 4 ingredients and stir-fry on high with 1/4 cup soy sauce until lettuce is almost clear, 2 to 3 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Follow directions on package for filling egg roll wrappers.
Seal and deep fry until desired brownness.
Serve with various sauces for dipping.

title: almond biscotti
directions: Place almonds in single layer on a cookie sheet.
Toast for 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Grease and flour two cookie sheets.
Stir together granulated sugar, flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Run through fingers to break up clumps.
Stir well.
Add butter.
With fingers blend till mixture looks like fine crumbs. Stir in lightly beaten eggs.
Add
almonds.
Knead till combined. Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Turn oven to 350°.
Divide dough in half. With floured hands, form two - 15 x 4 inch rectangles, about 1-inch thick. Brush with egg wash.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat on medium speed.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: super oatmeal brownies
directions: Mix oats, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a bowl.
Stir in melted butter.
Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture.
Pat oatmeal mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool 5 minutes.
Prepare brownie mix, using the fudgey recipe instead of the cake recipe on the box.
Add
the nuts.
Spread batter evenly over baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved oatmeal mixture.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool, cut in squares.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 7 to 10 minutes.
Mash with fork.
Serve warm or cold.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Whip the cream, but not too stiff; add lemon juice and honey and whip.
Dressing should not be very stiff.

title: semoran sunshine mulled cider
directions: Heat, but do not boil.
Simmer on low for 15 minutes.
Enjoy! Make some mulled cider for some Autumn family fun.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain all 4 cans of beans and put into large container.
Add diced celery, sliced onion and diced pimentos.
Pour mixture of sugar, canola or Wesson oil and vinegar.
Refrigerate until next day.
The longer this sits, the better it "gits!"

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate the cheese and put in a bowl.
Add pimento, sugar and Miracle Whip.
Blend until smooth and sugar is dissolved.
More or less sugar and Miracle Whip may be added or deleted, according to individual taste.
Spread the mixture on bread for sandwiches or on celery sticks for snacks.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Thaw broccoli in microwave.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan (do this in stove oven).
Chop onion.
Slightly beat eggs. Mix all together and pour into pan with melted margarine.
Bake at 325° until done.
This is also good when cold.

title: pork chop packets
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt until done.
Dip pork chops in flour and brown in pan with little oil.
Brown well on both sides.
Tear off 6 pieces of light weight aluminum foil about 14 inches long.
Divide the rice between the pieces of foil, placing rice in center of foil.
Top with pork chops.

title: mama's moist coconut cake
directions: Bake in three 9-inch pans (cool).

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash the cucumbers first.
Soak 1 bushel cucumbers overnight in alum powder.
Rinse in clear water.
Pack in jars with 1 piece of dill to each jar.
Heat to boiling point the vinegar, 1 quart water and salt.
Pour over pickles and seal.

title: pepperoni frittata
directions: In medium skillet, saute onions in oil until tender. Add zucchini or broccoli and cauliflower.
In bowl beat eggs and cheese until blended.
Add pepperoni.
Pour over vegetables in skillet.
Cook over low heat about 15 minutes until set.
Cut into pie shaped wedges to serve.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Debone and chop chicken, reserving 2 cups broth.
Mix in bowl the chicken broth, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and spaghetti. After thoroughly mixed, add chicken.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Drizzle butter over crackers and sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rotel cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Generously grease a 10 inch iron skillet. Combine cornmeal mix, flour, taco seasoning, Rotel, onions, egg, milk, and oil.
Mix well. Stir in cheese. Pour into prepared iron skillet.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes or until cornbread is delicately browned and is set in the center.
Turn out of skillet immediately.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add margarine. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each one.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chris' cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 cups sugar, eggs and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Punch holes in cake.
Heat to boil the milk, 1 cup sugar and butter and boil 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Pour over cake.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes; put through ricer while still warm.
Roll a marshmallow in potatoes, then roll in crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is melted and almonds coated.
Cool and break apart.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix together cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in chopped onion and chopped beef.
Warm in oven proof bowl at 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy in a large mixer bowl. Mix on lowest speed of mixer until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Press a candy kiss firmly on each cookie.

title: four bean burger bake
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain off excess fat. Combine meat mixture with remaining ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yogurt shake
directions: Put the yogurt, fruit and vanilla in a blender and mix until the drink is smooth.
The juice from the fruit should dilute the yogurt and make it drinkable.
If not, add a little milk.
Add a teaspoon of honey and taste.
Add more as needed (it will depend on how sweet the fruit is).

title: garden district broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli and cut the stalks lengthwise into thin pieces. In a heavy skillet, heat the olive oil and add a layer of sliced onion, tomatoes, black olives and anchovy.
Top with a layer of the broccoli and sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Repeat the process until all is used up, reserving a few pieces of anchovy.
Pour in the red wine.
Cover the skillet and cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until broccoli is just tender.
Garnish with remaining pieces of anchovy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken breast roll-ups
directions: Line a 3-quart casserole dish with 12 slices of dried beef. Wrap each piece of chicken with slice of bacon; lay on top of dried beef. Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken. Wrap dish in foil and chill overnight. Cook, uncovered, in 275° oven for 3 1/2 hours. Serves 12.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Crumble bread.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Stir until mixed well. Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add tomato mix.
Dot top with butter and bake in hot oven at 425° approximately 1 hour.
Should brown on top.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add to pudding mix 1 quart softened vanilla ice cream.
Mix well.
Pour pudding/ice cream mixture over crumbs in pan.
Spread on 1 carton Cool Whip.
Crush 3 Butterfinger bars and mix with remaining cracker mixture.
Sprinkle on top. Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water and add jello until dissolved. In a separate bowl mix sugar cornstarch and water. Mix well and add to jello mix. Stir and boil until thickened. Cut the bottoms off of whole, cleaned strawberries and place in pie crust in standing up position. Let jello mixture cool 10 - 15 min., pour over strawberries and let set. Top with cool whip and enjoy.

title: spicy swiss steaks
directions: Rub salt, allspice and pepper well into steak.
Dredge meat with flour.
Pound in flour with edge of plate.
Heat shortening in heavy casserole.
Brown meat quickly on both sides.
Add onions and tomatoes.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours. Check occasionally for moisture.
If necessary, add a little hot water.

title: karo fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on wire rack about 10 minutes.
Calories:
1 gram.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a lightly buttered casserole. Sprinkle top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, bell pepper and sugar. In a small pan, mix together vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt; bring to a rolling boil. Cool slightly. Pour over cabbage mixture; stir well. Refrigerate.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix margarine, corn meal, flour, salt, milk and egg; bake 25 minutes at 400°.
When done, break in crumbs and add saltine crackers, onion, broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well all ingredients until soupy.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and marinate for 24 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Mix sugar, sour cream, Cool Whip and milk.
Add angel food cake.
Add strawberries with glaze on top (not mixed).

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat 2 minutes. Add dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and chips. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drop by tablespoon 2-inches apart on ungreased sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on pan for 1 minute, then put on wire racks.

title: grandma brugger's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla together with mixer.
Add flour, soda, salt and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
