directions: *Mushrooms, celery, bell pepper, green onions, carrots, broccoli florets, seeded tomatoes, cauliflower, squash, cucumbers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Let cream cheese set out 30 minutes to soften.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread in flat dish.
Mix cocktail sauce and shrimp.
Pour over top.
Serve with Sociable crackers.

title: ranch beans
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in bacon grease.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish.
On top of mixture, place the topping.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix margarine, 1 egg (beaten with fork) and yellow cake mix. Press crumbs into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix 1 egg (beaten with fork), condensed milk, vanilla, Bits 'O Brickle and pecans. Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and then cut into bars.

title: hawaii baked beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Pour into deep baking dish.
Add ketchup, sugar, beans and pineapple.
Stir well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: great-grandma lucille's sweet corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, making sure it is all combined. Do not overbeat.
Pour mixture into a greased pan and bake at 425° until top is brown.

title: four-bean salad soup
directions: Saut sausage 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Drain excess fat. Add tomatoes, beans and cilantro; mix well. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Garnish with cheese, if desired. Serves 6.

title: feed-em-all cake
directions: Mix cake mix with Egg Beaters instead of eggs and 1 1/2 tablespoons canola oil.
Spray two 9 x 13-inch pans and one 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Spread on drained pineapple.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Mix pudding, milk and softened cream cheese in large bowl with electric mixer (will be slightly lumpy).
Spread over bananas. Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle coconut.
Keep in fridge.

title: lamb shanks(easy and tasty)
directions: In casserole dish, place desired number of lamb shanks and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix (do not add water).
Cook, tightly covered, in oven at 225° for 4 to 5 hours, until fork-tender.

title: lemon-dill salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except vegetable oil. Shape salmon mixture into 6 patties. Heat 1 1/2 to 2-inches of oil in a heavy skillet until hot. Fry patties, turning once until golden brown, about 8 minutes; place on paper towel to drain. And there you have your very own tasty lemon-dill salmon patties.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until crumbly. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Mix and knead on a floured surface. Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 2-inch circles. Dip in melted butter. Fold in half and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 1 hour.
Place in a 425° oven for 12 minutes.

title: phildelphia ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze as you normally do.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve each package of jello in 1 cup boiling water separately*.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to each.
Put lemon jello in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 35 to 45 minutes.
Boil milk and add sugar; dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water, then add to milk mixture.
Add vanilla to sour cream, then add to milk mixture.
Blend well with mixer (this is white).
Add 1 1/2 cups white mixture to pan of lemon jello after jello has set up firm. Refrigerate and set.
Add orange - set, 1 1/2 cups white mixture - set, lime - set, white - set and red - set.
Be sure to stir white mixture a little before measuring each 1 1/2 cups.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put icing on while hot.

title: cod fish fritters(bacalaitos)
directions: Soak the cod fish in water for two hours to remove part of the salt.
Remove bones and skin and shred into small pieces.
Mix flour, baking powder, garlic, oregano and water and add the cod fish.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonful and deep fry until crispy. Remove and drain on absorbing paper.
Makes 24.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Combine cookies and margarine; reserve 1/4 cup for topping, if desired.
Press remaining cookie mixture onto the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions except use only the 1 3/4 cups milk.
Immediately stir in peanut butter and chocolate.
Fold in dessert topping.
Spread mixture evenly over cooled crust.
Top with reserved cookie mixture. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: lemon buttered chicken
directions: Melt butter and add lemon juice.
Pour over cut up chicken placed in a shallow pan.
Use 1/2 of butter and lemon juice mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn and baste with remaining lemon butter.
Bake for 40 more minutes or until tender and evenly browned.
Serve on bed of watercress brightened with lemon wedges.

title: white frosting
directions: Mix first 5 ingredinets well with mixer.
Add vanilla and egg white and beat for 5 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, fill crust and chill for several hours.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs. Add sour cream, stir in sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, vanilla and salt. Mix well. Stir in apples. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes. Meanwhile combine 1/4 cup butter, 1/3 cup brown sugar and remaining flour. Sprinkle over top of pie. Return to oven for 25 minutes or until filling is set. .

title: sand tarts (drop)
directions: Mix together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Work in flour.
Drop a teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° until cookie looks slightly darker around edge, approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from sheet before they cool. Yields about 2 dozen.

title: sunday morn casserole
directions: Place hash browns in a 13x9 greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham, cheese, onions, peppers, mushrooms.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper together.
Pour over ham mixture.
Bake covered at 350° for one hour.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: burgundy beef stew
directions: Cook bacon in heavy casserole over medium heat until golden brown.
Remove casserole and drain.
Pour off all but 2 Tbsp. grease.
Increase heat to medium high and brown beef on all sides. Transfer beef and bacon to plate.

title: korean yukke mando
directions: Brown beef and pork; drain.
Add onions, carrots, m.s.g., garlic, celery salt and shredded cheese.
Put water on table and lay egg wraps in the water to keep them from sticking to table. Fill wrap and fold into diamond shape.
Deep fry.
To dip these, use soy sauce or A.1. sauce or sweet and sour sauce or barbecue sauce.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Add the beaten egg yolks, bread crumbs, lemon juice and seasonings to the flaked salmon.
Mix thoroughly and fold in beaten egg whites.
Mold and bake about 1/2 hour in a 350° oven. Crumbs over loaf make it brown nicely.

title: springtime lime salad
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly, then stir in Pet milk.
Chill until thick as unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a pan or mold; chill until firm.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush cookies.
Blend in sugar.
Mix in butter (melted) and stir in orange juice.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cake:
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar and dressing at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Blend in zucchini and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased 12 cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: beef short ribs polynesian
directions: Remove bones from meat and cut into 3-inch squares.
Apply meat tenderizer, following label directions.
Combine soy sauce, tomato sauce, oil, sugar, salt, pepper, garlic, green onion and sesame seed in shallow pan.
Add meat and marinate in this mixture overnight in fridge, turning to coat all sides.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a sauce pan and let come to a slow boil.
Cook for 15 minutes.
The longer it cooks the hotter it gets.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into well buttered baking dish.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: norma's potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain and mash.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Beat just until combined.
Spoon mixture into lightly buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until heated.

title: chicken rice artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice as directed, but omit butter. Cool. Add onions, green pepper and olives. Drain artichoke hearts. SAVE MARINADE and mix with mayonnaise and curry powder. Blend well. Add artichoke hearts which have been cut in half and diced chicken to rice mixture. Toss with dressing. Add mushrooms. If a little dry, add a bit more mayonnaise.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients (except bacon, if used). Bake uncovered about 40 minutes at 350 degrees. Broil to crisp bacon, if used.

title: champagne punch
directions: Chill the wine and champagne.
Hull strawberries and put into punch bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar. Add bottle of Claret and allow to stand for 1/2 hour.
Add champagne, ice ring and 16 friends. Enjoy!
Serves 16.

title: apple cake
directions: Dredge pecans in 1/2 cup flour.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and oil, add eggs and vanilla; beat.
Stir in dry mix, fold in apples and pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: parker house rolls
directions: In a large bowl, allow water or milk to cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast over water or milk.
Add sugar, soft shortening, salt and eggs.
Add 3 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Work in rest of flour, one cup at a time.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl, turn dough over to cover top, cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again until double, about 30 minutes.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter.
Make crease across each with back of knife.
Fold so top half slightly overlaps.
Press edges together at crease.
Place close together in lightly greased pan.
Let rise until light (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package in two layer pans.
Let cool. In a large punch bowl, crumble 1 cake layer and then add a layer of coconut, pineapple, pie filling and nuts.
Crumble second layer and repeat.
Pour pineapple juice over top and top with cool whip. sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices; add to apples.
Fill 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 minutes.
If apples aren't tart, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice or grated lemon peel, if desired.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat eggs, milk, and sour cream.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into dish, bake until set but moist; about 35 minutes.
Serves lots.

title: ham bone soup
directions: Boil bone for a few minutes, then add ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well. Set aside.

title: crabmeat sycamore
directions: Alternate layers of crabmeat, cheese and artichokes in greased casserole.
Spoon cream sauce evenly over the top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: grandma's mustard pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in sterilized jars and fill with the mixture. Shake often.

title: fruity fruit cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and line with wax paper.
Mix fruit and nuts together by hand.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with fruit.
Beat eggs with vanilla or rum flavoring; stir into other mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on rack in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove.
Cool again.
Wrap in foil.

title: country style zucchini
directions: Prepare in a skillet (and serve in it too).
Fry bacon crisp; remove, drain and set aside.
Drain some of the bacon fat from pan. Slice onions into skillet; partially fry.
Slice zucchini and add to skillet.
Mix onions and zucchini; season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook (medium to low heat); stir occasionally.
Cook until zucchini is tender, but not limp.
Crumble bacon over the top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve with a smile.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs and onion; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Spread mixture in a 9-inch pie pan to form a pie crust.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: soda biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Blend in shortening; stir in milk.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll out and cut 1/2-inch thick with biscuit cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Place the cream cheese in the center of a serving dish.
Drain the crabmeat well.
Spread on the top of the cream cheese.
Pour the cocktail sauce over all of it. Serve with crackers.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into 9 x 13 pan, saving 1/2 cup for topping.

title: pastel fruit cookies(cookie press cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Press onto sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: red fish - baked
directions: Fillet fish.
Place skin-side down in baking dish; salt and pepper.
Rub generously with olive oil.
Sprinkle liberally with Italian seasoning; add a little onion and garlic powder.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce; dot with butter and garnish with onion rings.
Bake at 400° until flesh flakes easily with a fork.
Takes about 30 to 45 minutes, depending on size of fish.

title: party pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons of juice for dressing.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Mix Stove Top and margarine together.
Put half of it in bottom of dish.
Mix chicken and soups together.
Put on top of mix.
Put the rest of Stove Top mix on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients all together for one minute.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper. Makes 50 to 60 cookies.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper, garlic salt, onion salt, pepper, chili powder and oregano.
After this is all browned, add the remaining 5 things.
Cook 6 hours or longer.

title: tangy corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours, tossing occasionally.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix hamburg, rice, salt and pepper; form into 8 to 10 balls. Place in baking dish.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in oleo for 5 minutes.
Add tomato soup.
Pour over meat balls; cover dish with cover or foil and bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours. Remove cover a few minutes before taking from oven to brown meat. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: soda bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Knead on a lightly floured board for 2 to 3 minutes (dough should be smooth).
Shape into round loaf and place in a well-greased 8-inch cake pan.
You also can use a cookie sheet.
Before placing in the oven, cut a cross on top of the loaf with a floured knife.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until the top is a warm brown.
Let cool and slice thin.
Do not be concerned that the cross has formed an opening on the bread, this is as it should be.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Blend together with electric mixer.
Spread mixture onto a serving plate.
Cover with shredded lettuce.
Then add a layer of chopped tomatoes.
Lastly add the shredded cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: the rock cornish hens
directions: Clean and wash game hens; rub salt inside.
Cut vegetables into bite sized pieces.
Place hens in a Dutch oven; place 1/4 apple, 1 piece potato and 1 piece carrot in body cavity of each game hen (do not eat these later).
Season hens to taste; sprinkle onion, potatoes, carrots, beans and apple in a Dutch oven.
Pour beer and soup to make gravy.
Season lightly.
Cover; bake at 325° for approximately 90 to 120 minutes.
Usually done when vegetables are tender.

title: lobster and shrimp mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Heat soup and add gelatin.
Stir and cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, celery, onion, curry powder and 2 teaspoons dill or to taste.
Stir in Langostino's and shrimp.
Pour into 4 to 4 1/2-cup mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Chill overnight.
Unmold and sprinkle entire top with dill and paprika.
Garnish with kale.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture forms fine crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remainder over bottom of ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: kidney bean and rice salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the rice, beans, apple, avocado, sweet pepper, onion and parsley.

title: strawberry satin pie
directions: Cover bottom of cooled, baked crust with almonds.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Pour in pie crust.
Slice 2 1/2 cups of strawberries in half and arrange on top of filling, petal fashion.
Place a few whole berries in center.
Crush remaining berries.
Add water and cook for 2 minutes.
Sieve.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in berry juice.
Cook and stir until thick and clear.
Tint with red food coloring.
Cool slightly.
Spoon over strawberries. Refrigerate until serving time.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan; cook until soft and thick, stirring constantly.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well and cool.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a small mixing bowl add milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut smoked beef and onions up real fine and mix with cream cheese and add Miracle Whip and garlic salt.
Shape into a ball.

title: juicy hamburgers
directions: Mix well and shape in hamburgers and fry.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth; set aside.
Stir-fry chunks of chicken, add steamed vegetables.
Add reserved broth mix, bring to boil until thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Soften ice cream at room temperature.
Arrange crackers in 9-inch pan.
Stir juice into ice cream.
Fold in chocolate chips. Spoon evenly over crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Cover and freeze about 2 hours.
Makes 9 sandwiches.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook meat, bone and kraut together for 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste, bay leaf, chopped onion, chicken broth and tomatoes.
Cook 1 more hour.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt shortening. add brown sugar.
Stir until mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Check after 15 minutes.
Do not overbake. 350 degrees. 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 baking dish.

title: pistachio pound cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except chocolate syrup.
Pour 2/3 batter into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Add chocolate syrup to remaining 1/3 batter and pour over top of batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: custard puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to boil.
Add flour; stir until thick ball.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Drop on cookie sheet in a ball.
Should make 10 or 12.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes. Remove from oven; place on a wire rack.
Take a sharp knife and slit a small hole in top of puff.
Cool.
Fill with pudding.

title: memorial tea date balls
directions: Melt butter with sugar and dates; when sugar dissolves, cook slowly 8 to 10 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Mix well and roll into small balls.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar or roll in coconut.
Makes 12 dozen.
Keeps well in airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Lay 4 big chicken breasts into a baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup; cover all with foil.
Bake unopened 1 1/2 to 2 hours. If not brown enough, cook without cover 1/2 hour longer.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel and slice apples into baking pan. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and egg.
Sprinkle over apples and sugar mixture.
Melt oleo and pour over apples.
Add pecans if desired.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream. Yields 6 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar together until creamy and fluffy.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up.
Mix to a fluffy consistency.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake in large Bundt pan.

title: florentine crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together spinach, cheese and sausage in saucepan; stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Unroll dough; separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise (forming 32 triangles).
Spread each triangle with rounded teaspoonful of spinach mixture.
Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush dough with beaten egg, if desired.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix the above in punch bowl. Be sure to use equal portions of the juice and ale.
Add lime sherbet.

title: black bean soup
directions: Combine beans, ham hock and chopped vegetables
in a 5 to 6-quart pot. Add enough water to cover the ingredients by 2-inches. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour.
Let mixture stand at room temperature overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook parsley, garlic salt and onion in enough butter not to stick until brown.
Pour soups in to this mixture.
Cook broccoli and arrange in baking dish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and fold in slightly beaten eggs.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 12 small pies.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine rice, sugar, marshmallows, cherries, pineapple, mayonnaise and nuts.
Whip cream cheese with whipped topping. Fold into rice mixture.
Chill overnight and garnish with cherries.

title: baked steak
directions: Place steak in oven ready pan.
Spread A.1. steak sauce over all.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over steak.
Spread mushroom soup on top of all; cover tightly with cover or foil.
Let bake for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
This makes its own gravy.
Brown and delicious.
Enjoy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zu-canoes
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise and hone out insides to resemble canoes.
Saute the insides with onion and garlic in a little water.
Scramble the tofu and seasonings like eggs.
Mix together with the zucchini-onion mixture and fill the inside of the zucchini halves.
Arrange zucchini halves in a baking dish with extra filling around them and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lucy's shrimp lunch
directions: In saucepan, combine zucchini with onion flakes and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and shrimp and simmer 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Recipe equals fish protein lunch portion.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Add milk, return to boil, then remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Makes enough for a two layer cake.
Good on white or spice cake.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening mix, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat in mixer until creamy.
Beat egg into mixer.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; mix until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls about 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon, reserve one handful for crumbs.
Then add egg, sour milk and baking soda.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in graham cracker crusts. Chill.
(Makes 2 pies.)

title: low-fat low sodium broccoli-pea salad
directions: Thaw broccoli and peas, draining as much water as possible. Combine broccoli and peas; toss with lemon juice.
Add celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together. Stir in vegetables.
Add chopped eggs and egg whites and mix lightly.
Serve as individual salads or in lettuce lined bowls. Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water (1/4 cup); add flour and dash of salt.
Stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that does not separate.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add egg and beat with mixture until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Drop dough onto baking sheet using 1 level teaspoonful of dough for each puff.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove puffs from oven; cool and split.

title: quick chicken and dressing
directions: In a very large bowl, place cornbread; add chicken broth until juicy but not watery.
Add remaining ingredients, adding eggs last.
Stir until very mixed.
Pour into a large casserole or baking pan.
Top with cooked chicken pieces, if desired.
Bake 45 minutes at 400° until set, but not dry.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: durkee green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated.
Top with remaining onions and bake until golden.

title: pasta with roasted pepper sauce
directions: On baking sheet lined with foil, broil pepper 3 inches from heat source; turn frequently until charred on all sides.
Let stand until cool, then peel pepper.
Remove and discard stem and seeds.
Chop pepper and set aside.
In 9 or 10-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat; add garlic and saute, stirring often until browned.
Be careful not to burn.
Add tomatoes and liquid; cook and stir until mixture is heated thoroughly, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add roasted pepper, capers, olives and seasonings.
Simmer until heated, 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve sauce over pasta and sprinkle with parsley.

title: pickle kraut relish
directions: Mix together chopped kraut, onion and sweet pickle relish. Makes 2 jars (16 ounce size).
Will keep good in fridge.
Very good.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup pineapple and egg whites for icing.
Mix cake mix, pineapple and egg yolks.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti (cool under cold water) and combine with beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Put in pie pan or shallow baking dish. Top with sour cream.
Brown and drain hamburger and mix with spaghetti sauce.
Pour over sour cream.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes.	With a teaspoon, carefully hollow out the tomatoes.
Add the olive oil to a frying pan; fry onion, breadcrumbs, parsley and chives.
Add cheese near the end to melt. With a teaspoon, place stuffing in the hollowed-out tomatoes.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls. Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Put in plastic bag after frozen.
When ready to serve, heat in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
May cover with aluminum foil in oven to prevent drying out.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and check at 30 minutes.

title: breakfast or brunch casserole
directions: Cool sausage and mix with all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a large bowl beat milk and peanut butter until smooth. Add biscuit mix and vanilla. Mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls. Roll in sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Boil 4 cups water.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and glossy.
Blend in gelatin and Ivory liquid soap.
This keeps well and cleans up easy!

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat, onions and green pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, green beans, salt and garlic. Simmer while preparing crust.
Separate dough and press over bottom and sides of 9-inch ungreased glass pie pan.
Use 1/2 of cheese mixture mixed with egg to spread over crust.
Add meat mixture to crust.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and paprika to top of mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Crust will be golden brown. Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat milk in heavy saucepan until bubbles appear around edges. Add rice and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until milk is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir rice occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold whipped cream, almond and raisin gently into rice.
Chill at least 1/2 hour.
Serve with Loganberry Sauce.

title: hot wassail punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat and add the spices.
Let stand one hour.
Strain out the spices. Combine with juices and apple cider.
Heat to boiling and serve hot.

title: old vinegar pie recipe
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, egg, vinegar and water.
Cook in top of double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Line pie with pastry and bake in moderate oven 3 minutes.
Pour filling in crust and bake until brown at 350°. Makes one 8-inch pie.

title: cornish hens with brown rice stuffing
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil; add rice and cover.
Reduce heat and cook for 40 minutes or until stock is absorbed.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onion, pepper and apricots in butter.
Mix with cooked rice, almonds, salt and spices.
Salt and pepper hens, inside and out.
Stuff with rice mixture and place one bacon slice on top of each hen.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, basting often with pan drippings.
If not tender after 1 1/2 hours, cover and steam for final 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender in chicken stock.
Puree broccoli in blender or food processor, using small amount of stock.
Melt margarine and stir in flour.
Add most of remaining stock.
Heat until not too thick.
Add pureed broccoli and warmed milk.
If soup is too thick, more stock can be added.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add ice cream and pineapple with juice.
Chill until partly thickened (ice cream may cool it enough).
Add drained fruit cocktail.
Chill.

title: el paso burgers
directions: Mix chopped onion and pepper with taco mix.
Mix well with hamburger.
Divide meat into 8 equal pieces and make patties. Grill or fry until done.
Top with cheese slices, sour cream and salsa.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand for 1 hour, then mix Bisquick, melted butter and milk.
Add rhubarb mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.

title: pineapple freeze
directions: Combine sour cream, condensed milk, stir in regular milk and lemon juice.
Freeze in 1 quart container until 1/2 frozen.
Stir in drained pineapples.
Freeze firm and serve.

title: brisket with barbecue sauce
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Salt and pepper both sides and place in a large roasting pan, fat side up.
Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, hot pepper sauce and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over brisket and cover with a lid or aluminum foil.
Place in a 200° oven for 10 to 12 hours. After brisket has been cooking for 1 hour, check to see if sauce is covering brisket.

title: brownie mix in a jar
directions: Note:
You can make this ahead for yourself or decorate the jar and give as a gift with this recipe!

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Cook sausage and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, beans with liquid and broth.
Add basil; heat until boiling. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add zucchini and pasta; cook 10 minutes more.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Slice fruit in medium baking dish.
Take 5 or 6 pieces of light bread and remove brown crust.
Slice bread in strips.
May need more bread.
Lay on top of fruit and then pour mixture of remaining ingredients over bread.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mash the tuna thoroughly; mix to a smooth paste with the potatoes, cheese, eggs, parsley, garlic and seasoning.
Shape into flat cakes about 1/2-inch thick and 2 inches in diameter.
Dip in the bread crumbs; saute in the hot oil until golden.
Serve hot or cold; hot with tomato sauce and cold with mayonnaise.
Serves 6.

title: lazy sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortenings and sugars together.
Add the vanilla extract and egg(s).
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together; mix in with first ingredients.
Roll into balls and press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375°.

title: deer roast
directions: You will also need a browning bag.

title: meat and potato dinner
directions: Layer ingredients in order given. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Remove cover and continue baking until potatoes are done. Makes 6 servings.

title: coffeepot tea
directions: Fill a carafe up to the metal rim with water.
Pour into the coffeepot.
Place the tea bags into the upper portion of the coffeepot.
(Do not use a filter.)
Let cycle run through. Meanwhile, put sugar in a 2-quart pitcher.

title: tropical fruit slush
directions: Mix 1/2 of first 5 ingredients in a blender until pureed.
Add 8 to 10 ice cubes and blend on high until ice is totally crushed. Pour into three 8 ounce glasses.
Repeat with second 1/2 of mixture.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Cut core from cabbage.
Cook leaves in salted water for about 8 minutes to soften and for better handling.
Cool and separate leaves.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, turn out on floured board.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 2-inch squares and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Delicious with honey.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all together.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.
Bake in long cake pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together, except croutons.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potatoes and applesauce
directions: Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Spread a layer of applesauce on bottom of dish.
Add a layer of potatoes.
Then applesauce and then potatoes, etc., ending with applesauce on top with pats of oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 an hour.

title: deep dish chili pie
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and combine seasoning, beans and tomatoes.
Mix well, then top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, then add muffin mix and bake for 15 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small cubes and wedges.
Shake them in a bag with mixture of flour and Parmesan cheese.
Melt margarine in a glass dish.
Place potatoes in a single layer in dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour, turning them over halfway through cooking time.

title: "veg casserole"
directions: Add all ingredients, except pie shell.
Pour into baking dish and top with broken pieces of pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook all ingredients until tender in water, except bacon. Fry bacon.
Save 6 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Make white sauce of the drippings with 2 tablespoons flour and 2 cups of milk.
Add white sauce to soup.
Crumble bacon and add to soup. Heat thoroughly.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter about 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add carrots, bouillon and water.
Boil until carrots are tender.
Add peas.
Make a paste of flour and a little water.
Add to soup while stirring and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Heat, stirring frequently, but do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with crackers.

title: lithuanian pressed chicken
directions: Place chicken in soup pot seasoned with salt, pepper and onion.
Cover with water and cook over medium heat until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from liquid.
Remove skin and bones. Cut meat into small cubes.
Put meat back into liquid and cook for 1/2 hour more.
Remove chicken from pot.
Press chicken into a Pyrex dish.
Pour liquid just to cover chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled, sliced thin; garnish with parsley.

title: pie filling(one pie)
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour	together;
add	salt.
Beat egg yolks together,
pour into pan with sugar and flour.
Pour in milk, vanilla, butter;
mix chocolate with a little amount of warm water
and dissolve well; add to mixture.
Cook over low heat until
mixture is thick like a pudding.
Use same recipe for coconut
pie.
Use coconut instead of chocolate.
Use egg whites for topping.

title: french oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Mix all ingredients in a heavy 3-quart ovenproof pot.
Cover and bake for 3 hours or until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.
Stir occasionally while baking.
Remove and discard bay leaf before serving or storing.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, baking powder and flour.
Add eggs and beat well. Add balance of ingredients.
Pour into pastry shells and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake according to box directions.
Allow to cool for a few minutes, then with a straw make holes in cake.
Mix condensed milk and cream of coconut together and pour slowly onto top of cake, allowing mixture to fall into holes of cake.
Mix pineapple and cool whip together and spread over top of cake.
Top with coconut flakes.
Add pecans as desired and garnish with cherry halves.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Stir in soda and baking powder and enough flour to make stiff dough. Roll out on floured board, cut out with cookie cutters. Bake in medium oven until slightly brown. Don't over cook.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Saute chicken breasts, bacon and onion soup mix in butter. Add vegetables.
Place in a large cast-iron pot.
Add water.
Cook over medium-low heat for about 4 hours, until all water is gone. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oyster crackers
directions: In a large bowl, put in oil and add seasonings; mix well.
Add crackers and mix well until all of the oil is absorbed in crackers.

title: stewed beef with gravy
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together; roll beef in flour mixture.
Drop in hot oil and brown. Add water slowly to prevent lumping.
Simmer on low heat for approximately 30 minutes.
May be served over rice, noodles or as a meat course with mashed potatoes.

title: summer succotash
directions: Cut enough corn to measure 2 cups.
Mix beans, salt pork and onion in 3-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until beans are tender.
Stir in corn. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 5 or 10 minutes or until corn is tender. Drain.
Stir in half and half, salt and pepper.
Heat stirring constantly, just until heated through.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over stuffing mix.
Cook squash and onion for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain water and combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Fold in squash and onion with the shredded carrots.
Put half of stuffing in the bottom of the dish. Add by spoonfuls the vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle remainder of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: golabki(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Remove core from cabbage and boil briefly (just to slightly soften it and the leaves start to wilt).
Parboil the rice and mix with the raw ground meat and seasonings.

title: chicken dressing for a big bunch
directions: Crumble cornbread and white bread into large bowl.
Pour broth over bread.
Add water until liquid barely covers bread.
Set aside for 5 minutes, then use potato masher to cream mixture.
Add eggs. Mix thoroughly.
Add soup mix (should be consistency of cake batter).
Add onions, chicken, sage and pepper.
Pour into 1 large or 2 medium ungreased pans.
Cover top with oil.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown.

title: choco-cheese fudge
directions: Mix all except cheese and margarine.
Melt cheese and margarine in microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir melted mixture into other ingredients.
Put into buttered pan and chill.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Make dough from the hot roll mix, as the directions indicate. Preheat the oven to 350°.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve over salad topped with croutons.
Refrigerate leftover dressing.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Beat eggs in small mixer bowl.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in melted butter.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool in pan.
Frost if desired; cut into squares. Makes 16 brownies.

title: deviled veal continental
directions: Dust veal lightly with flour; mix with paprika, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add veal and saute quickly until golden all over.
Remove veal.
Add onion to pan drippings and saute few minutes.
Stir in consomme and mustard and cook to blend flavors.
Return veal to pan.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes until veal is tender.
Just before serving, blend in yogurt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom; sprinkle coconut.
Mix cake according to directions; pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together.
Stir in sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buffet meatballs
directions: Combine meat and 1/4 cup sour cream, ketchup, salt, pepper, garlic salt and oregano.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown in oil and pour off excess grease.
Add water, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Remove meatballs to a casserole dish.
Combine remaining sour cream, salt and dill in skillet which meatballs were cooked.
Heat and pour over meatballs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: spring soup
directions: Cook onion slowly in butter until delicately browned.
Add everything but water cress.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes.
Add water cress and boil 5 minutes longer.
A piece of water cress makes a nice garnish.
Goes well with roast beef.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter. Beat well. Mix in sifted flour, soda and salt. Shape into small balls and flatten. Bake on cookie sheet 9 minutes in moderate oven (375°).

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Adjust
peanut
butter
and honey to attain proper
consistency,
which should be slightly sticky. Shape into balls or
short	rolls.	Can
be rolled in coconut for sweeter taste.
Keep refrigerated in a plastic bag or jar.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape and bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: 24 hour bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Carefully rinse kidney beans with water. Thoroughly mix salad oil, sugar and vinegar.
Place beans in bowl; add salad oil, sugar and vinegar mixture.
Toss lightly until well mixed.
Cover and marinate 12 hours in refrigerator.
Add celery and onion and marinate another 12 hours.
Stir several times.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for 35 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken breast
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Mix crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Roll and dip chicken in crumb mixture.
Spray a 13 x 7-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover last 15 minutes to allow browning.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add cream mixture. Add more flour, if needed.

title: ovenless chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter and oats.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Cream together Crisco and oleo for 3 minutes, until fluffy. Add sugar and mix well.
Blend in milk and vanilla; beat 5 minutes.
Do not heat milk too hot or it will separate frosting.

title: "creamy" carrot soup
directions: Heat oil in a heavy pot; add onion and cook until soft.
Add broth, carrots and rice.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Cool soup.
Puree soup in blender.
Return to pot and heat gently.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: appetizer puffs
directions: Mix flour and salt, add margarine in until mixture starts to form a ball.
Blend in sour cream.
Divide dough into 4 parts. Wrap each part and chill several hours.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
On a floured surface, roll each section of dough into a 12x6 inch rectangle.
Sprinkle one half each with all remaining ingredients.
Fold over into a 6 inch square.
Cut the 6 inch squares into 2 inch squares and press the edges together. Continue until all dough is gone.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350 for 20-25 minutes.
Makes about 35.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in large skillet until beef is browned, stirring to crumble; drain. Stir in tomato soup and the remaining ingredients. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring mixture often.
Serve on buns.

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix the sugar and the cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in blueberries and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Keep blueberry mixture hot in oven.

title: spaghetti tropical
directions: Boil the planters for about 15 minutes.
Scoop out; cut in the middle and fill with spaghetti and meatballs.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Place in the oven for 3 to 3 minutes and serve hot.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown beef; set aside.
Cook chopped onions in small amount of oil.
Drain crumbled, cooked meat in colander.
Mix with all ingredients in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Cook slowly.
At the last, add mushrooms; mix (optional).
Serve the plates with cooked spaghetti.
Pour meat mixture over the spaghetti.

title: tacos
directions: Brown the beef and the onion in a heavy skillet, cutting the meat in very small pieces.
Add the rest of the ingredients (except the tortilla shells) and slowly simmer for 1 hour (can be 30 minutes but the longer it cooks, the better).
Fill the tortilla shells with this mixture and serve.

title: veal cognac
directions: Lightly flour veal and saute in clarified butter with pimentos, mushrooms and onions.
Add brandy and flame, burn alcohol and cream.
Reduce to desired consistency and add parsley and seasonings.
Serve over rice and noodles.

title: pocket stew(serves 20)
directions: Peel back cabbage leaves.
Place canned corned beef in center. Wrap in foil and cook.

title: lemon drops
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Blend rind and shortening.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add egg and beat well.
Add lemon juice and water.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry crumbled hamburger until brown; drain off grease.
Add green beans and the soup.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and top with shredded cheese.
Layer Tater Tots evenly over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until crisp and brown on top.

title: pizza bread batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 1 loaf. Grill some Swiss cheese between bread slices for a pizza style sandwich.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with Ritz crackers and drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dieter's dream apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice and cornstarch in a medium saucepan, stirring well.
Cook, covered.
Heat until thickened and bubbly, stir in margarine, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add apples, toss well to coat.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 8 slices, 167 calories per slice.

title: orange date cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a very slow oven at about 300° in a foil-lined tube pan.
Before taking it out of pan and while still warm, pour topping over it and let stand overnight in pan.

title: chicken with rice in puff pastry
directions: Cook rice and combine with 2 egg whites.
Roll out pastry puffs very thin.
Place about 1/4 cup rice on each pastry.
Place chicken on top of rice and fold up pastry.
Place fold on bottom of baking dish.
Can make ahead.
When ready to bake, brush top with egg yolk.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with cream of chicken soup, diluted with some milk.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender until frothy.

title: shoo-fly pie(wet bottom)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine the flour, brown sugar, spices, butter and salt and rub the mixture between the hands to form crumbs.
Dissolve the baking soda in the water and combine with the molasses.
Pour into the pie shell.
Sprinkle with the crumbs.
Bake
30 to 40 minutes, or until filling is set.
Serves 6.

title: sausage crescent rolls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Separate rolls into triangles. Spread with sausage and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Roll crescents and then brush tops with beaten egg.
Place rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese and olive sandwiches
directions: Combine cream cheese, olives, walnuts and mayonnaise.
Spread on 6 slices of bread.
Cover with remaining 6 slices.
Trim crusts.
Cut each sandwich into thirds.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender, 12 to 15 minutes. Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter or margarine and herbed stuffing mix.
Melt 3/4 stick butter in frying pan; add stuffing and mix well.

title: maidrites
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole(one quart)
directions: Pour the first 6 ingredients into greased casserole and top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all salad ingredients, except almonds and tomatoes, together with enough mayonnaise to obtain desired consistency. Taste; add more seasoning salt if necessary.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with toasted almonds and tomato wedges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic powders in a lightly greased skillet.
Add celery, mixed vegetables and soup.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover; top with noodles. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: oven french fries
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Place cooking rack on countertop. Peel potatoes. Cut into long 1/2-inch strips. Dry with paper towels. Place in large bowl. Add oil. Toss to coat. Place potatoes in single layer on unprepared baking sheet. Combine celery salt, garlic powder, pepper and paprika in small bowl. Sprinkle potatoes with half of seasoning mixture. Turn potatoes over. Sprinkle with remaining seasoning mixture. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and evenly browned, turning occasionally. Do not overbake. Remove baking sheet to cooling rack. Serve warm.

title: hawaiian lemonade(punch)
directions: Mix together the lemonade, water, apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Chill.
Pour in ginger ale just before serving.
Serves about 30.
Makes about 7 quarts.

title: winter soup
directions: Cook leeks until glossy in butter.
Add potatoes and carrots. Add water to cover.
Add seasonings.
Simmer 1 hour.
Liquify, heat and serve.

title: graham cracker cake *
directions: Combine soft butter, sugar and eggs (one at a time); beat thoroughly.
In another bowl, mix crushed crackers, baking powder and milk.
Add pineapple.
Add coconut to egg mixture, then mix together for 2 minutes.
Last, fold in black walnuts; stir with spoon until mixed well.
Pour in deep pan and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli rice cheese bake
directions: In small skillet, brown onion and celery in oleo. Combine rice, broccoli, onion and celery in a large bowl. Add soup and Cheez Whiz and mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil broccoli for 3 to 4 minutes; drain well. Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle on the cheese. Combine butter and bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top of the cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef-broccoli wellington
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, brown meat; drain well. Stir in Mozzarella, onion, sour cream, pepper and broccoli. Simmer 10 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Overlap long sides of 2 rectangles, 1/2-inch.
Firmly press to seal.
On ungreased cookie sheet, press or roll into 13 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spoon meat mixture in center of dough.
Bring long edges to center of filling slightly overlapping.
Pinch edges and ends to seal.
Repeat with remaining rectangles.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes until deep golden brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 3 cups water and cook until just tender. Mix flour with the same amount of water as milk; add seasonings and mix with vegetables.
Cook over medium heat (do not boil) until flour has been cooked.
Sprinkle parsley (optional) and serve 6.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add cracker crumbs (rolled fine), baking powder, pecans and vanilla. Fold in all as blended.
Butter pie pan.
Add mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool; top with sliced bananas.
Cover with 1 cup of whipped topping.
Put in fridge to chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until mixture is clear.
Stir in jello.
Cool.
Slice strawberries and place on baked or cooked pie crust.
Pour cooled mixture over strawberries and chill.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil.
Cook dressing and mix with cabbage.
Pack into containers and freeze.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Bring water to a boil in large soup pot.
Add vegetables, tortellini and rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer until tortellini are al dente.

title: barbecue salad(tomato aspic with personality)
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add tomato sauce and other ingredients.
Blend and pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: golden raisin soda bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar into a mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar and golden raisins, then add buttermilk, mixing to form a firm, but not too stiff dough.
Knead lightly on a floured surface and form into a slightly flattened round.
With a large knife, cut a deep cross about 1/2 of the way down to form 4 equal sections in the loaf.
Brush the top lightly with milk.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Puree strawberries in blender or processor.
Combine eggs and oil in a small bowl and whisk thoroughly.
Sift remaining ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Pour in eggs and puree; blend well, using a wooden spoon.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake until tester, inserted in center, comes out clean, about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool.

title: simmerman
directions: Use glass baking dish, 8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inches.
To cream cheese, add powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon water.
Spread on baked crust. Sprinkle generously with chopped nuts.
Spread pie filling over all.
Chill.
Cut in large squares.
Serve topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: orange-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender; cool and peel.
Arrange in greased baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and orange juice.
Boil until thickened; add butter or margarine.
Pour glaze over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved; cool to lukewarm, 105° to 115°.
Combine 3 cups flour and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add yeast, sourdough starter and milk mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer until mixture is smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, 85°, free from drafts, 50 to 60 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and gradually work in remaining 3 cups of flour to make soft dough.
Divide dough in half and roll each half into an 8 x 6-inch rectangle.
Starting at widest end, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Fold under ends and place in two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 hour and 30 minutes or until doubled in bulk. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until loaves sound hollow when tapped.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp; mix well with beater until a creamy consistency.
Fold in shrimp.
Serve with dip chips or snack crackers.

title: fried cornmeal mush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to boil 2 3/4 cups water, then add the cornmeal, water, salt and sugar mixture, stirring all the time.
Cook until thick.
Reduce heat, cover pan and cook 5 more minutes, frequently stirring.
Pour into loaf pan and cool, then refrigerate several hours.
Slice and fry in hot fat, slowly turning only once.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Whip cooked potatoes, combine rest of ingredients to potatoes and whip until light and fluffy.
Put in greased casserole dish. Bake in 300° oven 30 minutes.
Keep warm in oven until ready to eat.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine sliced strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar; stir gently. Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: blueberry sauce(microwave recipe)
directions: In 1-quart casserole, stir together lemon juice and cornstarch. Add sugar and salt. Stir in undrained blueberries. Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until thickened and clear. Serve over ice cream, pancakes, unfrosted cake or cheese cake. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: glorious morning muffins
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Then remaining fruits, nuts and veggies.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given; beat well.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and a wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Yields approximately 9 servings.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Cut the gum drops and nuts into small pieces. Roll in flour before adding. Mix.
Bake in sheet pan or long pan and cut into squares.
Roll in powdered sugar, if desired, after cutting. Bake at 325°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first layer ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch pan and press for crust.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Grate and drain cucumber.
Make Jello with hot water.
Place into refrigerator until syrupy.
Add sour cream to Jello and whip together.
Add cucumber and vinegar to mixture.
Return to refrigerator until set.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: In skillet, brown chicken and mushrooms in butter.
Stir in soup, water, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Simmer 10 minutes more until liquid is absorbed.
Stir often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mango shake(fat-free)
directions: Let mangos thaw for about 15 minutes.
Put mocha mix in blender, then add mangos and sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Add more mocha mix as needed for desired consistency.
Makes 2 large servings.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter and put in half and half.
Add cheese gradually, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cook 1/2 package fettucine noodles.
Add small pieces of steak, chicken or shrimp to sauce.
Pour over drained fettucine noodles.
Serves 4.

title: ranch stew
directions: 1. Cook ground beef, onion, and pepper till beef is browned.
2. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add the rest and freeze.
Slice and serve on lettuce.
My favorite frozen salad.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add 3/4 cup of pizza sauce, cheese, bread crumbs, garlic salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Combine meats; add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Press into 9-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Drain.
Spoon remaining pizza sauce over loaf; bake for 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: polynesian meat balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Roll into balls and brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Put all ingredients together; adding sour cream and cheese to individual taste. Simmer until rice is cooked.

title: star dust salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and cool until hard.
Cover with marshmallows.
Sprinkle pecans.
Beat egg until foamy; add sugar, pineapple juice and flour.
Cook until thick; cool and spread on top of marshmallows.
Mix heavy cream and cream cheese and spread on top.

title: cucumber cinnamon rings
directions: Put rings in lime water; let stand 24 hours.
Drain rings; wash in cool water.
Pour cold water over rings; soak for 3 hours and drain.
Add 1 cup vinegar, 1 tablespoon alum and 1 small bottle red food coloring.
Water to cover.
Heat and simmer for 2 hours. Drain.
Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: clipper chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Using electric mixer, beat first 6 ingredients in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, soda and salt in small bowl.
Stir into butter mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing apart.
Bake until cookies are golden brown, about 16 minutes.
Transfer cookies to rack and cool.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, butter, shortening, vanilla, eggs and add 1 cup of flour at a time.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Boil together sugar, milk and Karo and bring to soft-ball stage.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Beat with a spoon until color change begins to occur.
Stir in pecans, 1 tablespoon butter and extract.
Pour into pan, either buttered, lined with wax paper or a Teflon pan.
Top with melted chocolate.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: syrup cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, syrup, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and stir until mixed well.
Roll into balls.
Dip into sugar.
Press down slightly with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° until slightly brown around edges.

title: spinach and mushroom casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter. Add lite soy and cook as much as you like.
In an 8 inch square glass pan, layer spinach, 1/2 of the cheese, then the onions and mushrooms, and the rest of the cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake and split in 4 layers.
Mix pineapple, sour cream and sugar.
Set aside 1 cup mixture.
Spread remainder between layers, then mix Cool Whip with 1 cup reserved mixture.
Cover cake with this mixture.

title: gooey lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the cake mix, 1 egg and butter and press into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar thoroughly, then add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done (325° for glass Pyrex pan).
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: jello cake
directions: Blend cake mix, Jell-O, eggs, water and oil.
Beat well.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes, or until done.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix milk with corn meal and stir in salt and shortening. Cool.
Add baking powder and egg yolk and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Pour into greased pan and bake in hot oven 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 (8x8 loaf).

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Build up slight edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on crust.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Drizzle over apples.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are brown.
Serve warm.

title: jalapeno rice casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Broil, peel, seed and chop jalapenos; then stir into rice.
Spoon rice into lightly buttered shallow 3-quart casserole.
Spread sour cream over rice; then sprinkle cheese evenly over sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Yield:
20 to 24 servings.

title: wifey rice
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Add rice; stir well.
Add water and salt; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in green onions, basil, and thyme.
Sprinkle with cheese; garnish with thyme sprigs, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings (serving size 1 c.).
Prep time:
10 min.
Cook time:
23 min.

title: shrimp and eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in oleo.
Add shrimp, cook a few minutes.
Add eggs to eggplant.
Add shrimp mixture and toast.
Mix well. Pour in casserole and top with bread crumbs and dot with oleo.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Blend jalapeno pepper and bell pepper in blender.
Mix vinegar and sugar; add to pepper mixture.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring constantly, until it comes to a slow boil.
Skim foam.
Add green food coloring.
Add Certo.
Bring back to a boil.
Pour into jelly glasses.
Can be served with chips as a dip or on mascho or other Mexican dishes.
Also very good on vegetables.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with water, strawberries, bananas and pineapple. Pour 1/2 in dish and set in refrigerator to set up.
Top with sour cream, then add rest of mixture.
Refrigerate until set.
Double if you want to fill 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frozen fruit treat(children's)
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cups.
Freeze in the freezer until firm. Remove paper liners and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: texas barbecue
directions: Place meat in a foil pocket and pour liquid smoke over meat. Cover with minced onion and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Close foil pocket.
Place pocket in crock-pot on low. Cook 12 hours. Remove meat from foil. Discard juices.
Refrigerate meat for 12 hours. Slice meat thinly and return to crock-pot.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: chicken-n-ritz casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and pull from bone.
Mix all ingredients together and put in pan.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top of dish and bake at 375° until bubbling (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: blender mayonnaise
directions: Place all ingredients in blender except the last 1 1/2 cups of salad oil.
Whip to desired consistency and slowly add the 1 1/2 cups of oil.

title: spiced blueberries
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Boil sugar, vinegar and tied spices 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add berries.
Simmer until tender.
Let stand overnight.
Pack into hot jars.
Boil syrup 1 minute.
Pour over berries.
Seal at once.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving size pieces.
Brown slowly in skillet; put in baking dish.
Melt margarine in skillet; add onion and cook until tender.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Set oven for 350°.
Put sauce over ribs.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: crockpot chuck roast
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in crockpot. Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours. Serve with mashed potatoes, baked potatoes or noodles.

title: gramdma morgan's stirred-up cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350 degrees.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: To make batter:
beat together egg, buttermilk, and honey; mix well together all dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients, including melted butter and mix well.
Pour half of batter into cast iron skillet, greased.
Layer browned meat, cheese and pepper.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 1/4 x 2-inch strips.
Mix flour with salt and toss with meat.
Heat butter in frying pan.
Add garlic and onion. Saute until garlic is lightly browned.
Spoon out and reserve. Add meat to same pan, a few pieces at a time.
Brown quickly and keep separate to prevent "stewing" meat.
When meat is browned, return all to pan.
Sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Blend well. Fold in sour cream.
Heat slowly, do not boil.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Garnish with mushrooms sauteed in butter.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and raisins.
Add this to the other ingredients which have been mixed well.
Fold in apples last.
Put in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at about 375°.

title: chili-mac
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Pour in chili beans, tomato sauce and 2 cans of water, tomato paste and 2 cans of water, Chili-O and other spices to taste.
Cook on low until boiling.
Pour in macaroni and cook until tender, stirring often.

title: peach dessert
directions: Place peaches in large dish. Put dry cake mix on top of peaches. Sprinkle brown sugar on top of cake mix. Pour melted butter evenly on top of brown sugar. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch glass dish empty 1 package of wafers, covering bottom and sides of dish.
Cut bananas into slices and place them on top of wafers (may use as many bananas as you like). Cover with remaining vanilla wafers.
Mix remaining ingredients in pot.
Cook over medium heat until pudding consistency.
Remove from heat and pour over top of wafers and bananas.
All of pudding should fit after allowing it to penetrate to bottom.

title: green dip
directions: Mix together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in unbeaten egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and rolled oats.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine sifted powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Spread chocolate evenly.
Drizzle with peanut butter mixture.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet.
Add all other ingredients to the meat, except the cheese.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's lemon icebox pie
directions: Crush about half the vanilla wafers. Set aside the remaining whole wafers. Combine crushed wafers and butter. Add more wafers or butter to achieve desired consistency. Press mixture into bottom of pie pan. Line sides of pie pan with whole vanilla wafers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Use regular loaf pan or 3 small loaf pans.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add the egg.
Add the bananas, flour, powder, soda and salt. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Trim
fat
from
chicken
and
place in a 12-inch Dutch oven. Rub
chicken with salt inside and out.
Sprinkle pepper in cavity. Rub garlic and thyme on outside of bird.
Tie bird and
spread margarine
on
outside.
Roast
for
2 1/4 hours. Replenish
coals halfway through cooking time. Cook on medium heat.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg and salt.
Add American cheese.
Stir this into drained macaroni.
Bake in a greased casserole for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Sprinkle top of pie with crushed graham crackers.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Do not soak.
Combine all ingredients together in pressure cooker and cook for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 4 quarts.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, rolled oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter in mixing bowl.
Mix on low speed until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crawfish-cornbread dressing
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery; saute for 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, paprika, thyme and mustard.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add stock and bring to a boil.
Add crawfish and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in cornbread and cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: fun pizza(child snack recipe)
directions: Variation:
To decorate pizzas, add beef, Canadian bacon or pepperoni.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cauliflower bacon salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cheese together for dressing.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Toss dressing and vegetables lightly. Keeps well in refrigerator for several hours. Broccoli flowerets may be substituted for cauliflower or added.
Carrots and red cabbage may be added for color.
Add milk to dressing mixture for a thinner dressing.
Serves 4-6.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use paper liners or grease 18 muffin cups.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat margarine with sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy, about 4 minutes.
At low speed, add flour mixture with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove muffins to wire rack.
Let cool. May be sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
May be baked in king size muffin cups (6).

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and halve potatoes.
Mix cheese, flour and salt together. Roll each half potato in butter and then in cheese-flour mixture. Place in shallow pan in oven and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes until browned.
Cover to prevent more drying.

title: roulades of beef with crabmeat stuffing
directions: Trim fat from steaks.
Place steaks between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Flatten to 1/8-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Cut each steak into 6 rectangles.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Stir until yeast is completely dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended. Turn out onto a well-floured board.
Knead 10 minutes or until elastic and smooth.
Place in a greased bowl.
Refrigerate until needed.
(Keeps for a week.)
To bake, roll out, cut and place in a preheated 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water. Add pie filling and pineapple. Let stand in fridge. Mix sour cream, cream cheese and sugar in mixer. Use as the topping after jello is set. Sprinkle nuts on top (optional).

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Mix all and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: waldorf slaw
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; chill. Toss with next 5 ingredients. Garnish with walnuts. Makes 2 quarts.

title: "oh, so good" microwave fudge
directions: Put chocolate chips, milk and butter in microwavable bowl. Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Return to microwave and cook another 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from microwave. Add marshmallows.
Stir in gently.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and chill.
Makes 2 pounds!

title: corn-bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn and put in a long baking dish. Mix the celery
soup
and
sour
cream.
Pour over corn and beans. Top with
the
grated cheese and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Pour on top of this the melted butter. Bake in a 350° oven until it bubbles and the cheese and crumbs are brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix with mixer.
Place in a casserole dish.

title: chess pie
directions: Place crust in pan. Place in 350° oven for 2 or 3 minutes. Remove and cool. Cream butter and sugar. Add other ingredients. Mix well. Pour in pie crust. Bake in 325° oven until knife comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Place flour in shallow dish, egg wash in shallow dish and bread crumbs or cornmeal in shallow dish (3 dishes).
Dredge tomato slices in flour and shake off excess. Dip in egg wash. Drain excess, then coat with seasoned bread crumbs. Shake off excess.
Heat oil in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
