When hot, add tomatoes in single layer and cook several minutes, until golden, then turn. Cook, remove to drain on paper toweling and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix egg, flour and sugar together (with your hands) until grainy.
Pour sliced peaches into pan.
Sprinkle the flour mixture over the peaches.
Melt margarine and pour over flour mixture. Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter quickly. Add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook, stirring occasionally to hard-crack stage (300°). Watch carefully after 280°. Quickly stir in coarsely chopped nuts. Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil. Spread candy into ungreased pan. Cool thoroughly. Turn out on waxed paper; spread with half the chocolate. Sprinkle with half the finely chopped nuts. Cover with waxed paper; invert. Spread with remaining chocolate; sprinkle with remaining nuts. If necessary, chill to firm. Break into pieces.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening thoroughly. Add buttermilk and yeast, dissolved in water.
Mix with spoon until all flour is moistened.
Roll out onto floured surface to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits.
Bake at 400° on cookie sheet for 12 minutes.
This dough will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix in bowl sugar, salt and flour.
Bring oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water to a boil; add to sugar and flour.
Add to mixture the remaining ingredients.
Bake in sheet pan, greased and floured, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: blend o' cheese mold(makes generous quart cheese mold)
directions: Soften gelatin in
cold water.
Dissolve over low heat. In blender, shred
the
Cheddar,
Mozzarella
and
Blue cheese until coarse.
Beat cottage cheese and sour cream until smooth and creamy.
Combine the 2 mixtures and add remaining ingredients. Blend until
smooth,
scraping sides and bottom of bowl occasionally.
Add softened
gelatin and beat until thoroughly blended.
Pour into mold.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight for best results.
Unmold
and
serve
with
assorted crackers and crisp,
colorful
vegetable
nibblers.
(Top
with
grated Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese,
cup
each, with a dash of crumbled Blue cheese, if desired.)

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In microwave bowl or Pyrex dish, place the first 3 ingredients.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 4 more minutes.
Stir and add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes more to lightly brown.
Remove and add soda.
Stir and spread on buttered 9 x 13-inch piece of foil.
Break when cool.

title: cheese struedel
directions: Grate cheese.
Add chilies and cottage cheese.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Pour into well-greased 3-quart baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Place meat in a roasting pan.
Spread the mushroom soup over the meat.
Sprinkle the mix over the top (do not add salt).
Add as many potatoes and carrots as you like and 3 cans of water. Cover the roasting pan in 300° oven for 3 hours.

title: easy prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out dough as if making fried pies.
Put apples on 1/2 of biscuit dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Fold over and crimp edges.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Boil sugar, margarine and soft drink.
Pour over pies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add flour and make rich brown roux.
Add onions, scallions and garlic.
Stir-fry for 10 to 12 minutes over moderate heat until golden brown.
Return sausage and add remaining ingredients except broth and stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Add broth.
Bring to a boil, then turn to lowest heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Uncover and stir well. Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally to dry out.

title: jello mold
directions: Combine ingredients, cool, pour into mold and chill.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Melt
and
let	cool
the
unsweetened chocolate.
Sift together
the
flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar 1/4 cup at a time. Beat well.	Add chocolate and salad oil.
Add dry ingredients, mixing at low speed.
Fold in zucchini and chopped nuts.
Bake in a
10-inch	greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes or bake in 4 small loaves for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Heat small amount of oil in a large saucepan.
Fry chicken until brown.
Drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
Drain and add taco seasoning.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes and green onions.
In a large bowl, pour refried beans and spread.
Top with hamburger meat, onions, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
When ready to serve, pour French dressing over the top of mixture and top with barbecue corn chips.

title: friar's bay restaurant bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and sugar.
Let set until it bubbles.
Add this to yeast then add flour to make soft dough. Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double.
Knead again and shape into rolls or bread loaves.
Rolls bake in about 45 minutes; loaves in about 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain juice from corn and beans.
Mix first 8 ingredients together and put in 2-quart size casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Crush Cheese Nips into melted oleo and spread as topping on casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Layer in buttered Bundt pan. Melt margarine; mix with sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Slowly stir at least half the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; continue stirring until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with pie meringue.

title: chili con queso casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and salt.
Line bottom of baking dish with 4 tortillas.

Spread with layer of 1/3 soup and milk mixture, 1/3 onion and chili mixture, 1/3 browned ground beef and 1/3 cheese. Repeat layers until all is used, ending with grated cheese on top. Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Chop all vegetables and combine all ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until tender.
Good with cornbread.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease (not oil) cookie sheets.
In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 42 to 48 cookies, 147 calories per 2 cookies.

title: pasta fagoli
directions: Sort and rinse beans in cold water.
In a 3-quart pan, add 4 cups cold water.
Let come to a boil.
Drain beans and add 8 cups cold water to beans.
Add large clove garlic and let come to boil again.
Lower heat to simmer.
Cook beans approximately 30 to 40 minutes or until al dente.
Do not overcook.
Set aside until ready to add to pasta.
Beans could be cooked several days before and refrigerated until ready to use.

title: recipe for eight pastie crusts
directions: Mix together the flour, lard and salt.
Beat egg in measuring cup, then add vinegar and 1 cup water.
Work, then divide dough in eights.
Roll and put in favorite pastie mixture.

title: dorothy's molasses taffy
directions: Cook molasses, sugar and water to 272° or until a small amount of mixture cracks when dropped into cold water.
Stir frequently. Remove from heat.
Add soda and butter, stirring just enough to blend.
Pour into shallow greased pan and let cool enough to handle.

title: peppermint cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend cheese, milk, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add sugar, beating until frosting is smooth and of spreading consistency.
If necessary, stir in additional milk, one teaspoon at a time.
Stir in 3 drops red food color and 2 tablespoons crushed peppermint candy.
If desired, sprinkle top of frosted cake with crushed peppermint candy.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers in deep skillet until onions become clear.
(May use lard, olive oil, bacon grease or any type of oil you choose.)
Add sliced or diced sausage, diced up chicken (chicken may be cooked in advance or leftover fried chicken with skin removed is good also.
Can boil chicken and pick it when its cooled.)
Save broth for later, or turkey, leftover from Thanksgiving or Christmas time.
Stir this until all is hot.
Now add rice.
Stir and let cook for 10 minutes.
Add chicken broth (liquid should be twice the amount of rice).
Season with salt and pepper and if you like cayenne pepper.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and make into 1 1/2-inch round balls.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes; pour off fat and put in crock-pot.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and molasses. Sift dry ingredients and add. Roll in 1/2-inch balls and dip in sugar. Bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple, pudding and sour cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: ice cream
directions: Blend first five ingredients.
Pour into one-gallon ice cream freezer.
Add
milk and start churning.
Remember to use rock salt mixed
with your ice.
Cut up fresh fruit and add it to the mixture
for an extra special treat;
peaches, bananas or any kind of berries are my favorites.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix gelatin, 1/4 cup sugar and salt in medium saucepan.
Beat together egg yolks and milk.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Place over low heat until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peppermint. Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold in gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add enough green food color to make a nice shade.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm. Garnish with cherries.
Delicious.

title: kabobs
directions: Add or pour all ingredients over 2 1/2 pounds of stew meat. Let marinate 4 hours or overnight.
For barbecuing, alternate small onions, green pepper pieces and fresh mushrooms with stems on skewers.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine softened butter, oil, sugar, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Cream well.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and beat 1 minute.
Mix flour, soda and cream of tartar together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375° or until edges are lightly browned.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Lay the pound cake on the bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In the same bowl as the Jell-O, put the strawberries in.
Pour the Jell-O and strawberries over the pound cake.
Mix in some Cool Whip; make sure it's even.
Then put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cream.
Add egg yolks, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (deep dish).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot and add enough water to cover.
Cook slowly about 2 hours.

title: tropical banana punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil and then cool completely.
Add bananas, pineapple juice, orange juice, water and lemon juice. Freeze mixture.

title: hot cheese 'n chiles
directions: Place chilies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Beat eggs together with milk and pour over cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: quick chinese chicken(stir-fried chicken a la orange)
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet over medium heat.
When hot, add soy sauce and garlic salt.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order: jello, sugar, water, cranberries, orange rind and pecans.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Put juice and water in bottom of 8-cup percolator.
Add other ingredients in top of the percolator basket.
Perk for 10 minutes. Serve hot.

title: berry sour cream jello salad
directions: Thaw berries.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Heat juice; add jello and dissolve.
Take off heat.
Add pineapple and berries.
Put 1/2 mixture in serving bowl.
Put remainder in refrigerator; keep stirring so it doesn't set.
When the bottom is set, put on sour cream.
Add remaining jello. Refrigerate until top has set.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken in small amount of water, alt, one carrot and celery and/or onion (optional).
Shred chicken after boiling. Deep fry Py-mei-fun in hot oil until lightly golden.

title: molasses shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Set aside.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Combine 4 remaining ingredients.
Alternate layers of crumbs and liquid mixture in pastry shell, ending with crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 20 minutes longer or until firm.

title: cousin bernadine's strawberry cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water, allowing this to stand until gummy.
Mix together 2 egg yolks, 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup milk.
Add this to the gelatin mixture; cook for 20 minutes and let cool.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Beat 10 minutes.
Add flour alternately with milk; add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done in a tube or Bundt pan.

title: crunchy lemon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cereal, lemon peel and salt.
Dip chicken in egg white.
Coat with cereal mixture.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch pan which has been sprayed with no stick cooking spray. Bake for 20 minutes or until cooked through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pepper salad
directions: Quick, easy and great to take to picnics or parties.
Mix well and refrigerate for at least 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with Ritz crackers or your favorite or thinly sliced stick bread.
Make double recipe if Anna Marie is around.

title: seafood and pasta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, italian salad dressing and cheese in a large bowl; blend well. Add peas, pasta, imitation crabmeat, broccoli, green pepper, tomatoes and onions; toss gently to mix. Cover, refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Press gently with hands.
Cut out biscuits with biscuit cutter.
Preheat oven to 410°.
Place biscuits in a greased iron skillet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: meat balls
directions: Make meat balls from the first five ingredients.
Boil a whole cabbage for 5 minutes.
Take whole leaves and wrap meat balls in them.
Chop up remaining cabbage in small pieces and place on bottom of pan.
Lay meat balls wrapped in leaves on top.
Pour chopped tomatoes on top and add water.
Let simmer about 45 minutes.

title: company mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and beat.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: golden baked chicken
directions: Place chicken on a rack in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush on chicken.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Brush chicken with margarine mixture once or twice during baking.
Serves 4.

title: fast football franks
directions: Combine ketchup, pepper, jelly and pineapple. Cook over med. heat, stirring until jelly melts. Stir in one lb cocktail franks. Serve warm with toothpicks. Can be put in crockpot to keep warm.

title: easy fudge frosting
directions: Mix and boil until thick
over low heat.
Add about 3/4 pound powdered sugar.
Will frost a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: easy hawaiian torte
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add egg, crushed pineapple and vanilla. Mix well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Turn into 9-inch square pan, greased and floured on bottom.
Combine coconut and packed brown sugar and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Clean legs from skinned bull frogs.
Sprinkle liberally with salt and pepper.
Combine milk and egg; beat well.
Dip legs into egg mixture; then coat well with flour.
Place in medium hot melted Crisco.
There should be at least one-inch of grease, as legs are best when fried rather quickly, about 4 to 6 minutes, turning once. Drain on absorbent paper.
Serves 4 to 6. Smaller legs are more tender.

title: lite chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Place in baking dish.
Top with sour cream.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350°, covered and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In 3-quart container, heat olive oil.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Set aside.
Brown meat; drain and add to onion mixture. Mix thoroughly.
Crush tomatoes.
Remove pulp.
Add to mixture. Add tomato paste, water and all seasonings.
Bring to slow boil. Be careful not to burn.
Lower heat and allow to cook down about 1-inch from top of container or until sauce thickens to your liking.
Makes about 6 cups.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for several hours.
Pour into a hollowed out rye loaf.

title: mom's tacos
directions: Fry hamburger, drain off grease.
Add salsa and simmer for 15 minutes.
Heat refried beans, cook corn tortillas or heat flour tortillas.
Add meat to tortillas, beans, vegetables and sour cream. Enjoy.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend the milk with the next 4 ingredients until slightly thickened.
Add enough food coloring to give the mixture a pleasant pale green color.
Pour into prepared 8-inch graham cracker crust and chill for 6 hours before serving.

title: wesley best pickles
directions: Drain pickles; RESERVE 3 CUPS JUICE. Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and 4 drops Tabasco to this juice and store in refrigerator. Put a layer of pickles back into the jar. Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar, 1/5 of the garlic and 1 teaspoon Tabasco on the pickle layer. Do this 5 times. Put the lid on the jar and turn it upside down. Turn it every day for 5 days. Separate into pint jars. This will fill 7 pints. Pour the juice to the top of the jars; put on the lids and refrigerate.

title: frozen fudge delight
directions: Crumble cookies and put in pie plate.
Mix in butter and press down.
Freeze for about 30 minutes.
Mix ice cream for about 20 seconds.
Mix peanut butter and Heath bar into ice cream.
Put on cookie sheet. Freeze for about 4 hours.

title: three bean salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in vinegar, stir in oil.
Add other ingredients.
If desired, add mushrooms, olives, pepperoni, chunks of cheese, etc. to make like an antipasto.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: "skinny shake" for oven fried chicken
directions: Empty crumbs into bowl. Stir in salad oil with a fork or pastry blender. Cover and keep in refrigerator to use as needed. Use about 1/2 cupful per 2 1/2 pounds cut up chicken.
Season it to suit yourself (onion salt, m.s.g., paprika, pepper, garlic powder, celery seed, bouillon powder, dried herbs, etc.).

title: grilled herbed biscuits(method:  grill)
directions: Combine the milk and Italian seasonings in a bowl.
Add the biscuit mix; blend according to package directions.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick on a floured surface; cut with a round, 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place around the outer edge of a grill.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil, shiny side down.
Grill for 5 minutes. Turn and grill 2 minutes longer, or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: pumpkin custard pudding
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in other ingredients.
Turn into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm. Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all and chill.
Ready to serve.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in a deep bowl.
Add quartered chicken pieces and marinate in refrigerator for at least 12 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade and place on grill over low coals.
Cook until tender, turning and basting with marinade.

title: muscadine pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell and cool. Top with Cool Whip.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: ham
directions: Place meat, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow baking pan. Score top of ham in a diamond pattern.
Insert whole cloves in center of patterns.
Bake, covered, in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: God uses broken things.
It takes broken soil to produce a crop, broken clouds to give rain, broken grain to give bread and broken bread to give strength.
It is the broken alabaster box that gives forth perfume.
It is Peter, weeping bitterly, who returns to greater power than ever.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water, Karo, salt and peanuts.
Cook until the peanuts almost stop popping.
Then turn off the fire and add butter and soda.
Pour into greased pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple and juice to a boil. Remove from heat, then add Jell-O.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into a dish. Cover and chill.

title: mud pie
directions: Press in 10 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° to a light brown. Check every 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sausage burritos
directions: Cook and stir pork, onion and green pepper over medium heat until pork is done, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Prepare tortillas as directed on package.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons beans down center of each tortilla.
Divide pork mixture among tortillas. Top with lettuce.
Fold 2 opposite sides of each tortilla over filling.
Fold 1 end up and about 1/4 over folded sides.
Serve with taco sauce, if desired.

title: bread sticks or crackers
directions: Blend oats until fine.
Remove from blender.
Blend remaining ingredients (except flour) until smooth.
Stir together all ingredients.
Roll dough between hands to form into sticks (use flour on hands to keep from sticking).
Bake at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients (makes 1 dry quart when mixed).
Add to hot water according to desired taste.

title: creamed chipped beef
directions: Tear beef into small pieces.
Melt butter or margarine in frying pan or saucepan.
Add beef.
Saute until beef is hot and turning brown.
Sprinkle flour and pepper over beef.
Stir to coat meat.
Add milk slowly while stirring.
Cook and stir constantly over low heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Serve over toast or mashed potatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy fish chowder
directions: Select whiting, flounder or blackfish.
Wash and place in cold water to cover.
Chop celery and onions fine.
Add these, bay leaf and salt to cut up fish.
Bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes. When cool, bone and skin fish.
Strain broth.
To broth, add diced potatoes.
Boil until potatoes are done.
Add fish, cream and milk.
Simmer 5 minutes; serve with crackers.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over margarine in dish.
Heat fruit with 1/4 cup of sugar if it isn't presweetened.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with chicken and sprinkle cheese on top. Mix soup, mayonnaise, onion, celery and milk.
Pour over cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke over the meat.
Salt meat on both sides with celery, garlic and onion salt.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Drain.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 275° covered for 4 hours.
For the fifth hour of baking, pour on 1 bottle barbecue sauce and bake uncovered.

title: soft serve chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients; place into ice cream maker.
Make as usual, but will not usually stop ice cream maker.
Ready in about 45 minutes.
This recipe will be soft and will refreeze well.

title: chicken manicotti with chive cream sauce
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water, then drain well again.
Steam celery, green pepper and onion until slightly tender.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Pierce warm cake with toothpick. Pour condensed milk and caramel topping over cake.
Spread on whipped topping.
Sprinkle with candy bars.

title: one cup cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8 baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour over melted butter.
Add 1 pint sweet fruit or 1 can of pie filling of your choice.
I like Thank You brand the best because of the thickness (peach, blackberry, apple).
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter. Add graham cracker crumbs. Work until moist. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 pan.

title: butter oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order listed.
Line cookie sheets with tinfoil.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon batter onto cookie sheet spacing two inches between.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on foil on cake racks, peel from foil when cooled.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add yogurt, eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl blend baking powder, soda, salt and flour.
Mix in yogurt mixture.
Fold in lemon rind.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan.
Pour in batter. Bake 45 minutes until done.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: date candy cookie balls
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; stir in sugar until dissolved. Add dates and continue cooking.
Add milk, salt and eggs to mixture; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies to mixture; cool slightly.
Roll in chopped coconut; place on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; pour into a 9-inch pie pan. (I use aluminum, lightly greased.)
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, ice with whipped cream.

title: crispix goody
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and syrup in medium saucepan. Bring to full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir well.
While previous mixture is heating; mix Crispix and nuts together in microwave safe container.
Pour boiling mixture over Crispix mixture and stir to coat.
Microwave on high for 5 minutes.
Stirring every 1 to 1-1/2 minutes.
Spread out to cool.
Break up.
Store in airtight container.

title: presidential potatoes from the "white house"
directions: Use as many potatoes as needed.
Peel and rub each in olive oil.
Slice about 1/2-inch thick, not all the way through. Sprinkle with oregano and parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° until done. Cover before baking with aluminum foil.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Simmer (cover) slowly until meat is tender enough to mash. Serve on buttered toast buns.

title: sprinkle cookies
directions: Crumble up graham crackers and sprinkle in a 9 x 11-inch pan. Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Alternate pouring layers of the 3 bags of chips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top.
If desired, sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 325° until chips have melted.
If mixture is too runny, let sit or put in refrigerator to harden.
This recipe is rich and quick.
It can also be frozen and saved.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and place in pan of pork and beans.
Sweeten with brown sugar - sweeter the better.
Some might not like it too sweet.

title: apple pizza pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients and gradually add water.
Roll out or press onto pizza pan.
Make sure crust is up edges of pan.

title: oriental vegetable stir-fry(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, combine green onion, celery, pepper, carrots and margarine.
Cover.
Microwave on Full power for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in peas, bean sprouts and mushrooms.
Cover.
Microwave on Full power for 2 to 3 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Drain.
Mix soy sauce and ginger and pour over vegetables.
Microwave on Full power 1 minute.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy cinnamon spread
directions: Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, cinnamon & vanilla with mixer.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature with the brownie nut bread in this cookbook.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Flour and grease baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° (preheat oven).

title: quick and easy rocky road fudge
directions: Line an 8 inch square pan with foil, extending foil over edges.
Lightly butter foil.
Melt chips in large saucepan over very low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in frosting.
Add marshmallows and mixed nuts; mix until well coated. Spread in buttered foil-lined pan.
Refrigerate until firm. About 1 hour.
Remove fudge from pan by lifting foil; remove foil from fudge.
Cut into squares.

title: spiced fruit compote
directions: Stir spices into peach juice in saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove saucepan from heat and cool.
In large bowl, combine pears, apricots, cherries and brandy.
Pour cooled spiced syrup mixture over fruits.
With rubber spatula, gently toss mixture to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, stir in banana chunks.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mamie's crumb cake
directions: Beat margarine and brown sugar until creamy.
Add dry ingredients.
Remove 1 cup and set aside.
Add sour milk with soda to remainder of mixture.
Add egg and vanilla.
Grease 9-inch round or square pan and fill.
Add crumb topping and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until toothpick can be removed clean.

title: apple-nut topping
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, brown sugar and ground cinnamon in a small bowl; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in apple and pecans.
Cover and refrigerate. Serve with gingersnaps, shortbread cookies or pound cake.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: frozen corn
directions: Bring to boil; remove from heat and set in pan of cold water until cool.
Do not drain.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: quick potato soup
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients except chives. Cook on High for 4 1/2 minutes until bubbly, stirring twice.
Top with chives.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana boats
directions: Slit open one side of the skin of the banana.
Fill the crack with bits of marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Wrap each banana in aluminum foil and heat in a 400° oven for 7 minutes.
Eat with a spoon straight out of the skin.

title: etouffee
directions: Note:
Can add Ro-Tel tomatoes, if desired.

title: cream of salmon soup
directions: In medium pot, heat butter until foamy.
Add flour and stir well with wooden spoon.
Cook on low heat for 1 minute.
Slowly add both broths, whisking until thickened.
Add cream, tomato paste, tomatoes and basil.
Cook on low heat 4 to 5 minutes.
Add salmon, salt and pepper.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes (until salmon is cooked).
Do not boil!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Drain the green beans. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Slice potatoes and layer on bottom, then layer green beans, next add thick onion slices and spread soup on top.
Place chops on top, then sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over all.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: kielbasa with romaine lettuce
directions: Boil kielbasa with 1/2 cup water.
At first boil, then simmer 10 minutes.
Drain and cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Cook red pepper and onion until soft.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats (let stand 20 minutes). Add oleo, brown and white sugars.
Beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in medium size loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: The night before, place all 6 ingredients in a jar and cover tightly.
Shake until well blended.
Refrigerate.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt butter in a pie plate.
Add pecans to pie plate and roll them in the butter.
Roast for 2 minutes on High in microwave. Take out and stir.
Do the same thing 3 times.
After they have cooled, add just a little seasoned salt.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Drain pineapple and add enough water to equal 2 cups.
Add jello mixture.
Chill.
When thickened, fold in cheese, carrots, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into mold that has been rinsed in cold water.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on a platter and serve plain or make a dressing of mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: open house punch
directions: Blend bananas with orange juice.
Mix with fruit juices, sugar and water.
Freeze in containers that fit in punch bowl. Two hours before serving, put frozen juice in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over it.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cube all meat. Mix together chicken, sour cream, soup, chiles and cheese.
Layer mixture between corn tortillas and top with more Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in large bowl.
In a flat casserole or lasagne pan, put a layer of Doritos and a layer of mixture.
Put more Doritos on top, then cover with grated cheese. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in sheet cake pan or layer cake pans.
(Best if pans are sprayed with Baker's Joy.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour; keep checking on cake.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; fold in thawed strawberries and juice.
Add pineapple with juice along with nuts.
Pour half of mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish; chill until firm. Spread top with sour cream.
Gently spoon remaining half of gelatin mixture on top of sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix altogether; then pour over top and mix well.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Dip washed and dried chicken in melted butter.
Dredge in a bowl of dressing mix, cheese and crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in greased baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together; stir in sugar. Beat eggs and add with remaining ingredients, stirring just to mix well.
Bake in two greased and floured 9x5x3 inch loaf pans at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs.
Feed in bread and milk. Add pineapple and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour, milk, cream, salt and pepper. When thick, add cheese, mushrooms and pimentos and cook 2 minutes. Add potatoes, diced very small and cook 2 more minutes. Put in buttered casserole dish. A half hour before serving, cover top well with croutons. Sprinkle top with paprika. Heat in 325° oven 30 minutes or until croutons are brown. Dot with parsley and serve. Can make day before and heat just before serving.

title: fiesta corn bake
directions: Combine corn, carrot, onion and olives.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, sauce and 1 cup bread crumbs.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Toss remaining crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
May be garnished with additional sliced ripe olives. Serves 6 to 7.

title: sour cream spinach
directions: Cook spinach in 1/2 cup water for 8 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in sour cream, onion soup mix and sugar.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Serve.
